WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:34.372 align:middle line:90%


00:00:34.372 --> 00:00:36.830 align:middle line:10%
>> REGINA MEREDITH: The most
common complaint about Western

00:00:36.830 --> 00:00:39.850 align:middle line:10%
allopathic medicine is that it
doesn't take the whole person

00:00:39.850 --> 00:00:40.900 align:middle line:10%
into account.

00:00:40.900 --> 00:00:43.660 align:middle line:10%
Rather, it views disease
as an isolated event

00:00:43.660 --> 00:00:46.050 align:middle line:10%
to be treated in an
isolated fashion, which

00:00:46.050 --> 00:00:48.040 align:middle line:10%
is why most diseases,
particularly

00:00:48.040 --> 00:00:50.640 align:middle line:10%
those of a chronic
nature, persist.

00:00:50.640 --> 00:00:53.100 align:middle line:84%
Dr. Nita Desai chose
a different path.

00:00:53.100 --> 00:00:55.460 align:middle line:84%
Being of East Indian
descent, she was well aware

00:00:55.460 --> 00:00:58.670 align:middle line:84%
of the value of Ayurveda,
and she pursued her degree

00:00:58.670 --> 00:01:00.530 align:middle line:90%
in holistic medicine as well.

00:01:00.530 --> 00:01:02.600 align:middle line:84%
Dr. Desai learned
from the best of them

00:01:02.600 --> 00:01:04.970 align:middle line:84%
and is going to give us a
primer on the value of using

00:01:04.970 --> 00:01:08.260 align:middle line:84%
the Ayurveda principles of
opposites in our own health

00:01:08.260 --> 00:01:09.600 align:middle line:90%
practices.

00:01:09.600 --> 00:01:11.320 align:middle line:84%
Thank you for joining
us here today.

00:01:11.320 --> 00:01:13.810 align:middle line:84%
I know you're a busy lady, and
you're even between clients.

00:01:13.810 --> 00:01:16.310 align:middle line:84%
We were lucky enough to catch
you here in Boulder, Colorado,

00:01:16.310 --> 00:01:19.580 align:middle line:84%
because you are so clear
in your explanations

00:01:19.580 --> 00:01:21.490 align:middle line:90%
of the subject of Ayurveda.

00:01:21.490 --> 00:01:24.090 align:middle line:84%
I haven't found anybody
that is as clear as you.

00:01:24.090 --> 00:01:26.780 align:middle line:84%
Because you really do embody
both the East and the West,

00:01:26.780 --> 00:01:29.009 align:middle line:84%
and you can speak
to all of us on it.

00:01:29.009 --> 00:01:30.050 align:middle line:90%
>> NITA DESAI: Thank you.

00:01:30.050 --> 00:01:30.716 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah.

00:01:30.716 --> 00:01:32.634 align:middle line:84%
First of all, I
wanted to find out--

00:01:32.634 --> 00:01:34.300 align:middle line:84%
you come from an East
Indian background,

00:01:34.300 --> 00:01:37.980 align:middle line:84%
but in your family
was Ayurveda thought

00:01:37.980 --> 00:01:41.250 align:middle line:90%
of as a different way of being?

00:01:41.250 --> 00:01:42.450 align:middle line:10%
>> DESAI: Not really.

00:01:42.450 --> 00:01:45.080 align:middle line:10%
Most Indian households,
we use Ayurveda

00:01:45.080 --> 00:01:47.720 align:middle line:10%
as part of our lifestyle,
but we don't really

00:01:47.720 --> 00:01:49.780 align:middle line:10%
think of it as being Ayurvedic.

00:01:49.780 --> 00:01:52.150 align:middle line:10%
So the food, the
cooking, the spices,

00:01:52.150 --> 00:01:54.230 align:middle line:10%
the combinations of
foods, all of that

00:01:54.230 --> 00:01:55.890 align:middle line:10%
is just part of the lifestyle.

00:01:55.890 --> 00:01:57.910 align:middle line:10%
The daily routines,
things that we

00:01:57.910 --> 00:02:02.850 align:middle line:10%
do are very Ayurvedic
culturally but not really

00:02:02.850 --> 00:02:05.730 align:middle line:10%
something that we acknowledge
as being Ayurveda,

00:02:05.730 --> 00:02:07.080 align:middle line:10%
for the most part.

00:02:07.080 --> 00:02:09.699 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So you decided to
get your degree in Western

00:02:09.699 --> 00:02:10.370 align:middle line:90%
medicine.

00:02:10.370 --> 00:02:11.060 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: Yes.

00:02:11.060 --> 00:02:14.144 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And were you
having to, in your training--

00:02:14.144 --> 00:02:16.310 align:middle line:84%
first of all, give us an
idea about your background.

00:02:16.310 --> 00:02:18.470 align:middle line:84%
And also in your
Ayurveda training

00:02:18.470 --> 00:02:21.710 align:middle line:84%
you really trained with some
of the very best of them,

00:02:21.710 --> 00:02:23.010 align:middle line:90%
including Deepak Chopra.

00:02:23.010 --> 00:02:25.250 align:middle line:84%
But did you have to give
something of yourself

00:02:25.250 --> 00:02:29.830 align:middle line:84%
away when you were going through
Western medical training?

00:02:29.830 --> 00:02:33.410 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: Well, I started out
as a Western medical doctor,

00:02:33.410 --> 00:02:36.600 align:middle line:84%
so I guess that was my
framework when I started.

00:02:36.600 --> 00:02:39.480 align:middle line:84%
And I think it was
more of a journey

00:02:39.480 --> 00:02:41.840 align:middle line:84%
for me learning
Western medicine,

00:02:41.840 --> 00:02:44.450 align:middle line:84%
becoming a Western-trained
medical doctor.

00:02:44.450 --> 00:02:48.660 align:middle line:84%
And then I was lucky enough
in my residency program

00:02:48.660 --> 00:02:50.840 align:middle line:84%
to have a medical
doctor who practiced

00:02:50.840 --> 00:02:53.230 align:middle line:90%
Ayurveda who was a preceptor.

00:02:53.230 --> 00:02:55.910 align:middle line:84%
And so I kind of had
a glimpse of there

00:02:55.910 --> 00:02:57.430 align:middle line:84%
is something
different out there.

00:02:57.430 --> 00:02:59.700 align:middle line:84%
There's a different
way to practice.

00:02:59.700 --> 00:03:03.580 align:middle line:84%
It gave me a little glimpse
that there's something else out

00:03:03.580 --> 00:03:06.400 align:middle line:84%
there, though at the
time I was obviously

00:03:06.400 --> 00:03:08.270 align:middle line:84%
set to be a family
practitioner, and I

00:03:08.270 --> 00:03:11.940 align:middle line:84%
was in a residency program, went
out and got a regular old job.

00:03:11.940 --> 00:03:14.050 align:middle line:84%
And once I started
working, I really

00:03:14.050 --> 00:03:16.380 align:middle line:84%
realized that
close to 80% to 90%

00:03:16.380 --> 00:03:18.590 align:middle line:84%
of patients that were
coming to see me,

00:03:18.590 --> 00:03:20.670 align:middle line:84%
I really, really
couldn't help them.

00:03:20.670 --> 00:03:24.010 align:middle line:84%
I didn't have enough tools
or enough understanding

00:03:24.010 --> 00:03:25.925 align:middle line:84%
to help people with
their everyday problems.

00:03:25.925 --> 00:03:28.175 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Especially chronic
disease, I would assume.

00:03:28.175 --> 00:03:29.780 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: Especially
chronic diseases.

00:03:29.780 --> 00:03:33.140 align:middle line:84%
The remedies, the
drugs, the medications

00:03:33.140 --> 00:03:35.070 align:middle line:90%
really were Band-Aids.

00:03:35.070 --> 00:03:37.380 align:middle line:84%
They really weren't fixing
a lot of the issues.

00:03:37.380 --> 00:03:39.150 align:middle line:84%
And that's when
I started to look

00:03:39.150 --> 00:03:42.740 align:middle line:84%
a little deeper into other
ways of treating people.

00:03:42.740 --> 00:03:45.330 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Did that pain you
a bit as a Western medical

00:03:45.330 --> 00:03:47.880 align:middle line:84%
doctor, to see you could just
keep throwing prescriptions

00:03:47.880 --> 00:03:51.840 align:middle line:84%
at it, but the same people
would be back in a few months?

00:03:51.840 --> 00:03:54.922 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: It was difficult.

00:03:54.922 --> 00:03:56.880 align:middle line:84%
You want to think that
you're doing a good job,

00:03:56.880 --> 00:04:00.400 align:middle line:84%
and you want to have some sort
of satisfaction from your job,

00:04:00.400 --> 00:04:01.790 align:middle line:90%
no matter what you do.

00:04:01.790 --> 00:04:04.530 align:middle line:84%
And it just wasn't--
there was no satisfaction.

00:04:04.530 --> 00:04:06.700 align:middle line:84%
I felt like I wasn't
helping anybody.

00:04:06.700 --> 00:04:09.350 align:middle line:84%
There wasn't a sense
of value in what

00:04:09.350 --> 00:04:11.830 align:middle line:84%
I was doing at the
time for me personally.

00:04:11.830 --> 00:04:13.930 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: I can
understand that.

00:04:13.930 --> 00:04:16.279 align:middle line:84%
Now this is a little off
topic, but I'm always

00:04:16.279 --> 00:04:17.529 align:middle line:90%
curious about this.

00:04:17.529 --> 00:04:19.670 align:middle line:90%
What about your colleagues?

00:04:19.670 --> 00:04:21.950 align:middle line:84%
So many people are still
playing in the system.

00:04:21.950 --> 00:04:24.580 align:middle line:84%
And you can understand
job security, economics,

00:04:24.580 --> 00:04:26.460 align:middle line:90%
and all those basic motivations.

00:04:26.460 --> 00:04:30.100 align:middle line:84%
But did many of your
colleagues feel the same way?

00:04:30.100 --> 00:04:33.050 align:middle line:84%
Or is it just say, hey, this is
what the HMO says to prescribe,

00:04:33.050 --> 00:04:35.660 align:middle line:90%
that's what we're doing?

00:04:35.660 --> 00:04:39.320 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: I would say that the
majority of medical doctors are

00:04:39.320 --> 00:04:42.510 align:middle line:84%
beginning to realize there's
more out there and that they

00:04:42.510 --> 00:04:44.320 align:middle line:90%
need to open up their horizons.

00:04:44.320 --> 00:04:48.410 align:middle line:84%
Maybe some of them are being
forced, because their patients

00:04:48.410 --> 00:04:50.760 align:middle line:84%
are bringing in articles
and talking about things

00:04:50.760 --> 00:04:53.120 align:middle line:84%
and sort of pushing
the issue a little bit.

00:04:53.120 --> 00:04:55.800 align:middle line:84%
I would say when I went
through medical school

00:04:55.800 --> 00:04:57.930 align:middle line:84%
and when I went
through my residency,

00:04:57.930 --> 00:05:00.040 align:middle line:84%
holistic medicine
really wasn't that big

00:05:00.040 --> 00:05:01.520 align:middle line:90%
of a thing at that time.

00:05:01.520 --> 00:05:04.210 align:middle line:84%
So I would say that I was
in the minority of people

00:05:04.210 --> 00:05:05.936 align:middle line:84%
really looking at
something different.

00:05:05.936 --> 00:05:08.060 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: But you're seeing
a bit of a change now.

00:05:08.060 --> 00:05:08.770 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: Absolutely.

00:05:08.770 --> 00:05:09.180 align:middle line:90%
I think--

00:05:09.180 --> 00:05:10.100 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: That's encouraging.

00:05:10.100 --> 00:05:12.308 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: --a lot of younger
generation of physicians

00:05:12.308 --> 00:05:15.680 align:middle line:84%
already knows they have to
practice differently or else

00:05:15.680 --> 00:05:17.780 align:middle line:84%
they're just not going
to be successful.

00:05:17.780 --> 00:05:20.280 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: I interviewed one
woman a number of years ago who

00:05:20.280 --> 00:05:24.440 align:middle line:84%
was a gastroenterologist,
and she had many clients from

00:05:24.440 --> 00:05:25.690 align:middle line:90%
the age of five on.

00:05:25.690 --> 00:05:28.250 align:middle line:84%
And then she had the drug reps
coming through three, four,

00:05:28.250 --> 00:05:30.910 align:middle line:84%
five reps a day, bringing
baskets of sandwiches

00:05:30.910 --> 00:05:33.910 align:middle line:84%
and cookies for her
office workers and such.

00:05:33.910 --> 00:05:36.350 align:middle line:90%
And she had a thriving business.

00:05:36.350 --> 00:05:40.980 align:middle line:84%
But this one woman
came in regularly,

00:05:40.980 --> 00:05:43.900 align:middle line:84%
and she just kept getting
worse and worse and worse.

00:05:43.900 --> 00:05:45.567 align:middle line:90%
And finally, she disappeared.

00:05:45.567 --> 00:05:47.150 align:middle line:84%
She didn't see the
client for a while.

00:05:47.150 --> 00:05:50.200 align:middle line:84%
And the client came
back about a year later.

00:05:50.200 --> 00:05:53.119 align:middle line:84%
She'd lost a tremendous amount
of weight, in a good way.

00:05:53.119 --> 00:05:54.160 align:middle line:90%
She didn't recognize her.

00:05:54.160 --> 00:05:56.280 align:middle line:84%
She thought that they had
giving her the wrong file.

00:05:56.280 --> 00:05:57.029 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: Oh, wow.

00:05:57.029 --> 00:05:59.660 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And so she looked at
the woman, and the woman said,

00:05:59.660 --> 00:06:02.837 align:middle line:84%
"I'm here for one reason, to
tell you you were killing me.

00:06:02.837 --> 00:06:04.420 align:middle line:84%
And what I've done--"
and she told her

00:06:04.420 --> 00:06:06.466 align:middle line:90%
all the resources she had used.

00:06:06.466 --> 00:06:08.340 align:middle line:84%
Well, the long and short
of that is the woman

00:06:08.340 --> 00:06:10.460 align:middle line:84%
quit the business
after a short time

00:06:10.460 --> 00:06:12.340 align:middle line:84%
and went into a
whole different way

00:06:12.340 --> 00:06:14.260 align:middle line:84%
of working with
people holistically,

00:06:14.260 --> 00:06:15.630 align:middle line:90%
like what you're talking about.

00:06:15.630 --> 00:06:18.570 align:middle line:84%
And I thought it was a very
beautiful story and very

00:06:18.570 --> 00:06:20.725 align:middle line:84%
courageous because that
was a big hit financially

00:06:20.725 --> 00:06:23.052 align:middle line:84%
to close the doors
of that business.

00:06:23.052 --> 00:06:25.260 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: And that's what
it is for a lot of doctors.

00:06:25.260 --> 00:06:27.970 align:middle line:84%
Maybe many doctors might want
to do something different,

00:06:27.970 --> 00:06:30.480 align:middle line:84%
but medical school doesn't
really train us in nutrition.

00:06:30.480 --> 00:06:35.390 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't train us in so
much of the basic tools

00:06:35.390 --> 00:06:37.880 align:middle line:84%
that we need to do a
more holistic practice.

00:06:37.880 --> 00:06:40.080 align:middle line:10%
And so it's a huge investment.

00:06:40.080 --> 00:06:42.590 align:middle line:10%
You come out already with
a medical education, which

00:06:42.590 --> 00:06:44.290 align:middle line:10%
costs you a lot
of money, and then

00:06:44.290 --> 00:06:47.027 align:middle line:10%
to do all this extra
training is very, very hard.

00:06:47.027 --> 00:06:48.110 align:middle line:10%
>> REGINA: But you did it.

00:06:48.110 --> 00:06:50.054 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: Yes, I did.

00:06:50.054 --> 00:06:50.970 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Thankfully.

00:06:50.970 --> 00:06:53.350 align:middle line:84%
What I wanted to do
was talk about this.

00:06:53.350 --> 00:06:57.120 align:middle line:84%
This isn't a weird system
of medicine passed down

00:06:57.120 --> 00:07:00.890 align:middle line:84%
through the ages for
nonsensical reasons and lore.

00:07:00.890 --> 00:07:02.750 align:middle line:84%
Ayurveda makes sense
on a scientific level.

00:07:02.750 --> 00:07:04.880 align:middle line:84%
Give us some of
the basis for that.

00:07:04.880 --> 00:07:07.440 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: Well,
basically Ayurveda,

00:07:07.440 --> 00:07:09.160 align:middle line:84%
the reason I became
interested in it,

00:07:09.160 --> 00:07:12.960 align:middle line:84%
is because it really explained
things in a very logical

00:07:12.960 --> 00:07:13.700 align:middle line:90%
manner.

00:07:13.700 --> 00:07:17.500 align:middle line:84%
So many things that Western
medicine can't explain,

00:07:17.500 --> 00:07:20.510 align:middle line:84%
Ayurveda was able to come
in and explain to me why

00:07:20.510 --> 00:07:23.940 align:middle line:84%
these symptoms were happening
in a very logical manner,

00:07:23.940 --> 00:07:25.950 align:middle line:84%
in fact in a very
predictable manner.

00:07:25.950 --> 00:07:29.120 align:middle line:84%
So you could look at
somebody and almost predict

00:07:29.120 --> 00:07:31.160 align:middle line:84%
what their symptoms
were going to be.

00:07:31.160 --> 00:07:34.650 align:middle line:84%
So it really does have
a very scientific basis.

00:07:34.650 --> 00:07:37.000 align:middle line:90%
It believes in quantum physics.

00:07:37.000 --> 00:07:40.406 align:middle line:84%
So the science that
Ayurveda's coming out of

00:07:40.406 --> 00:07:41.580 align:middle line:90%
is the new science.

00:07:41.580 --> 00:07:43.260 align:middle line:84%
It is the quantum
physics science.

00:07:43.260 --> 00:07:46.920 align:middle line:10%
We believe in energy in matter
and that there's a relationship

00:07:46.920 --> 00:07:49.650 align:middle line:10%
there, and so we believe
that the energetic field

00:07:49.650 --> 00:07:52.220 align:middle line:10%
around the body also
affects the physical body.

00:07:52.220 --> 00:07:55.430 align:middle line:10%
And there's a lot of
research now in that field.

00:07:55.430 --> 00:08:00.110 align:middle line:10%
And we're really realizing that
it isn't just something way

00:08:00.110 --> 00:08:01.660 align:middle line:10%
out there in left
field, that there's

00:08:01.660 --> 00:08:03.230 align:middle line:10%
a lot of science behind it.

00:08:03.230 --> 00:08:06.640 align:middle line:10%
And Ayurveda kind of
follows in that footsteps

00:08:06.640 --> 00:08:09.880 align:middle line:10%
of being a very ancient,
over 5,000 years old,

00:08:09.880 --> 00:08:12.700 align:middle line:10%
science, and that's
kind of why it's

00:08:12.700 --> 00:08:14.120 align:middle line:10%
hung around for so many years.

00:08:14.120 --> 00:08:15.286 align:middle line:10%
>> REGINA: Because it works.

00:08:15.286 --> 00:08:16.470 align:middle line:10%
>> DESAI: It works.

00:08:16.470 --> 00:08:20.050 align:middle line:10%
It's based on some
real scientific facts,

00:08:20.050 --> 00:08:21.530 align:middle line:10%
and it definitely works.

00:08:21.530 --> 00:08:23.830 align:middle line:10%
>> REGINA: Well, most people
who have maybe dabbled,

00:08:23.830 --> 00:08:28.440 align:middle line:10%
like myself, a little bit
with Ayurveda can understand

00:08:28.440 --> 00:08:33.179 align:middle line:10%
the physical protocols of
opposites and so forth.

00:08:33.179 --> 00:08:35.890 align:middle line:84%
When you're talking about
acknowledging the quantum

00:08:35.890 --> 00:08:38.450 align:middle line:84%
field around the
body as well, you

00:08:38.450 --> 00:08:42.200 align:middle line:84%
must be also including a
mental/emotional component

00:08:42.200 --> 00:08:43.205 align:middle line:90%
in this practice.

00:08:43.205 --> 00:08:44.080 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: Absolutely.

00:08:44.080 --> 00:08:48.280 align:middle line:84%
Ayurveda's a mind,
body, spirit medicine.

00:08:48.280 --> 00:08:50.140 align:middle line:84%
So we look at the
physical body, we

00:08:50.140 --> 00:08:52.620 align:middle line:84%
look at people from a
mental/emotional point of view,

00:08:52.620 --> 00:08:54.320 align:middle line:84%
and we look at
them energetically.

00:08:54.320 --> 00:08:56.550 align:middle line:84%
And when I practice Ayurveda,
what I'm trying to do

00:08:56.550 --> 00:08:58.550 align:middle line:84%
is just like Western
medicine says

00:08:58.550 --> 00:09:01.980 align:middle line:84%
that you have a unique
constitution at the time

00:09:01.980 --> 00:09:05.460 align:middle line:84%
of birth from your parents,
at the time of conception

00:09:05.460 --> 00:09:08.750 align:middle line:84%
from your parents, you
inherited a unique constitution,

00:09:08.750 --> 00:09:11.000 align:middle line:84%
Western medicine
calls it genetics,

00:09:11.000 --> 00:09:13.230 align:middle line:84%
but then they don't
really do much with it.

00:09:13.230 --> 00:09:16.760 align:middle line:84%
You're told you have a
unique genetic makeup,

00:09:16.760 --> 00:09:19.110 align:middle line:84%
but then Western medicine
doesn't take that any further.

00:09:19.110 --> 00:09:21.720 align:middle line:84%
In Ayurveda, we look at you
from a physical point of view,

00:09:21.720 --> 00:09:23.390 align:middle line:84%
from a mental/emotional
point of view,

00:09:23.390 --> 00:09:24.890 align:middle line:84%
and from an energetic
point of view.

00:09:24.890 --> 00:09:27.630 align:middle line:84%
So we say that we really
need to figure out

00:09:27.630 --> 00:09:29.510 align:middle line:84%
what your energetic
signature is.

00:09:29.510 --> 00:09:32.020 align:middle line:84%
So at the time of conception
from your parents,

00:09:32.020 --> 00:09:34.226 align:middle line:84%
you're born with an
energetic signature.

00:09:34.226 --> 00:09:35.600 align:middle line:84%
And when I'm
practicing Ayurveda,

00:09:35.600 --> 00:09:38.440 align:middle line:84%
I have to find out what that
energetic signature is, I've

00:09:38.440 --> 00:09:40.650 align:middle line:84%
got to find out what's
gone out of balance,

00:09:40.650 --> 00:09:43.050 align:middle line:84%
and then I've got to really
help you to bring that back

00:09:43.050 --> 00:09:43.990 align:middle line:90%
into balance again.

00:09:43.990 --> 00:09:47.115 align:middle line:84%
And that's some of the basic
philosophy of Ayurveda.

00:09:47.115 --> 00:09:49.740 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And most of the time
when you do find a way to bring

00:09:49.740 --> 00:09:51.600 align:middle line:84%
that back into
balance or harmony,

00:09:51.600 --> 00:09:54.190 align:middle line:84%
is that when the chronic
diseases start reversing

00:09:54.190 --> 00:09:54.714 align:middle line:90%
themselves?

00:09:54.714 --> 00:09:55.630 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: Pretty much.

00:09:55.630 --> 00:09:58.510 align:middle line:84%
A lot of chronic diseases
from our point of view

00:09:58.510 --> 00:10:00.730 align:middle line:84%
is you've just kind of
gone off the path a little.

00:10:00.730 --> 00:10:04.010 align:middle line:84%
You've strayed
away from the kinds

00:10:04.010 --> 00:10:06.840 align:middle line:84%
of foods, the kinds of
lifestyle, the kinds of things

00:10:06.840 --> 00:10:08.260 align:middle line:84%
that you need to
be doing to keep

00:10:08.260 --> 00:10:11.180 align:middle line:84%
your particular
constitution healthy.

00:10:11.180 --> 00:10:13.050 align:middle line:90%
So we're very individualized.

00:10:13.050 --> 00:10:16.870 align:middle line:84%
We don't have any one
prescription for everybody

00:10:16.870 --> 00:10:19.330 align:middle line:84%
because we believe in
this individuality.

00:10:19.330 --> 00:10:23.030 align:middle line:84%
And we kind of have to tap
into your individuality

00:10:23.030 --> 00:10:26.060 align:middle line:84%
to be able to say, well, this
is what you should be doing,

00:10:26.060 --> 00:10:27.430 align:middle line:90%
and then you'll be healthy.

00:10:27.430 --> 00:10:28.270 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Mm hmm.

00:10:28.270 --> 00:10:28.860 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:10:28.860 --> 00:10:30.860 align:middle line:84%
Well, that's a nice
little beginning point.

00:10:30.860 --> 00:10:32.770 align:middle line:84%
Now we need to get
into some specifics

00:10:32.770 --> 00:10:34.940 align:middle line:84%
because I think
most people watching

00:10:34.940 --> 00:10:37.650 align:middle line:84%
this are looking to
hear and see and have

00:10:37.650 --> 00:10:40.000 align:middle line:84%
a little bit of
themselves reflected back.

00:10:40.000 --> 00:10:41.940 align:middle line:84%
And so it seems to
me the logical place

00:10:41.940 --> 00:10:45.090 align:middle line:84%
to start is with the
constitutions themselves,

00:10:45.090 --> 00:10:46.292 align:middle line:90%
called the doshas, right?

00:10:46.292 --> 00:10:47.000 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: Mm hmm.

00:10:47.000 --> 00:10:51.000 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And if we can start
out with the vata, pitta,

00:10:51.000 --> 00:10:54.850 align:middle line:84%
kapha, with vata first, and give
us an idea of what this person

00:10:54.850 --> 00:10:57.770 align:middle line:84%
is like so we can start
seeing glimpses of ourselves,

00:10:57.770 --> 00:10:58.910 align:middle line:90%
our loved ones, and such.

00:10:58.910 --> 00:10:59.690 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: OK.

00:10:59.690 --> 00:11:02.950 align:middle line:84%
So the doshas are
really energies

00:11:02.950 --> 00:11:06.990 align:middle line:84%
that control certain aspects of
what's happening in our body.

00:11:06.990 --> 00:11:09.740 align:middle line:84%
So the first dosha is
called the vata dosha,

00:11:09.740 --> 00:11:13.150 align:middle line:84%
and it really controls
the nervous system

00:11:13.150 --> 00:11:16.850 align:middle line:84%
or the electrical energy
system of the body.

00:11:16.850 --> 00:11:19.935 align:middle line:84%
People who are vata tend
to be very creative people.

00:11:19.935 --> 00:11:22.310 align:middle line:84%
They tend to be people who
have a lot of different things

00:11:22.310 --> 00:11:23.410 align:middle line:84%
that interest
them, and they like

00:11:23.410 --> 00:11:25.180 align:middle line:84%
to dabble in a lot
of different things.

00:11:25.180 --> 00:11:26.960 align:middle line:90%
They're open-minded, flexible.

00:11:26.960 --> 00:11:28.950 align:middle line:84%
They can see lots of
different points of view.

00:11:28.950 --> 00:11:32.000 align:middle line:84%
When the energy of vata,
though, goes out of balance,

00:11:32.000 --> 00:11:34.660 align:middle line:84%
it'll start to scatter
in an outward direction.

00:11:34.660 --> 00:11:37.310 align:middle line:84%
When that happens, you
start to feel scattered.

00:11:37.310 --> 00:11:39.320 align:middle line:90%
You start to feel ungrounded.

00:11:39.320 --> 00:11:41.160 align:middle line:84%
So mentally,
emotionally, you might

00:11:41.160 --> 00:11:43.160 align:middle line:84%
start to feel a
little bit of anxiety,

00:11:43.160 --> 00:11:48.000 align:middle line:84%
fear, worry, those
types of emotions.

00:11:48.000 --> 00:11:52.250 align:middle line:84%
You start to become what people
might call a space cadet.

00:11:52.250 --> 00:11:56.330 align:middle line:84%
You might get a little
spacey, basically ungrounded.

00:11:56.330 --> 00:11:58.520 align:middle line:84%
So you have a hard
time focusing.

00:11:58.520 --> 00:12:01.390 align:middle line:84%
And so that's sort of the
mental/emotional component

00:12:01.390 --> 00:12:02.182 align:middle line:90%
of what happens.

00:12:02.182 --> 00:12:03.640 align:middle line:84%
So when they're in
balance, they're

00:12:03.640 --> 00:12:04.856 align:middle line:90%
extraordinarily creative.

00:12:04.856 --> 00:12:06.730 align:middle line:84%
When they're out of
balance, they can kind of

00:12:06.730 --> 00:12:09.580 align:middle line:90%
get into this ungrounded place.

00:12:09.580 --> 00:12:12.590 align:middle line:84%
Physically, we say
that that vata dosha

00:12:12.590 --> 00:12:14.260 align:middle line:90%
is a very subtle energy.

00:12:14.260 --> 00:12:18.650 align:middle line:10%
And so the people physically
are these very light people.

00:12:18.650 --> 00:12:20.200 align:middle line:10%
They have light bone structure.

00:12:20.200 --> 00:12:21.820 align:middle line:10%
They're slim.

00:12:21.820 --> 00:12:23.530 align:middle line:10%
They're either very
large or very small.

00:12:23.530 --> 00:12:27.120 align:middle line:10%
They could be very
tall or very short.

00:12:27.120 --> 00:12:29.960 align:middle line:10%
>> REGINA: Let's say a
Nordic type of constitution,

00:12:29.960 --> 00:12:34.690 align:middle line:10%
with blue eyes, blond hair,
thin, tall, more pale skin.

00:12:34.690 --> 00:12:36.710 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: That might be vata.

00:12:36.710 --> 00:12:39.110 align:middle line:84%
I would say the
most important part

00:12:39.110 --> 00:12:41.299 align:middle line:90%
of that is the very small bones.

00:12:41.299 --> 00:12:42.465 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Small bones, yes.

00:12:42.465 --> 00:12:45.610 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: Very
delicate features.

00:12:45.610 --> 00:12:48.840 align:middle line:84%
Though vata has something
about irregularity.

00:12:48.840 --> 00:12:50.680 align:middle line:84%
Vata controls the
nervous system,

00:12:50.680 --> 00:12:54.410 align:middle line:84%
so it's really involved
in movement and change.

00:12:54.410 --> 00:12:57.200 align:middle line:84%
And so anything that
moves, anything that change

00:12:57.200 --> 00:12:58.719 align:middle line:90%
has to do with the vata dosha.

00:12:58.719 --> 00:13:00.260 align:middle line:84%
And so a lot of
times vatas will have

00:13:00.260 --> 00:13:02.160 align:middle line:90%
a little bit of irregularities.

00:13:02.160 --> 00:13:03.850 align:middle line:90%
Their face is not quite perfect.

00:13:03.850 --> 00:13:05.700 align:middle line:84%
There's just a little
bit of irregularity,

00:13:05.700 --> 00:13:07.982 align:middle line:84%
a little bit of
something not quite--

00:13:07.982 --> 00:13:09.440 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Not
totally symmetrical.

00:13:09.440 --> 00:13:10.273 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: --perfect.

00:13:10.273 --> 00:13:11.340 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:13:11.340 --> 00:13:16.560 align:middle line:84%
In general, they tend to be
thinner, lighter physically,

00:13:16.560 --> 00:13:17.670 align:middle line:90%
weak joints.

00:13:17.670 --> 00:13:20.370 align:middle line:84%
So vatas will very
commonly get joint issues.

00:13:20.370 --> 00:13:22.970 align:middle line:90%


00:13:22.970 --> 00:13:27.630 align:middle line:84%
Digestively vatas tend to have
a harder time digesting food,

00:13:27.630 --> 00:13:31.860 align:middle line:84%
so they tend to get constipated
very easily, gas, bloating,

00:13:31.860 --> 00:13:39.810 align:middle line:84%
those types of issues, dryness,
dry skin, dryness in the colon.

00:13:39.810 --> 00:13:42.670 align:middle line:84%
Those are the kinds of issues
you would see with vata dosha.

00:13:42.670 --> 00:13:46.860 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: In this profession,
among a lot of people who are

00:13:46.860 --> 00:13:51.730 align:middle line:84%
writers and producers and
in this particular world,

00:13:51.730 --> 00:13:54.920 align:middle line:84%
not just as journalists
but entertainers as well,

00:13:54.920 --> 00:13:57.010 align:middle line:90%
you see a lot of vata energy.

00:13:57.010 --> 00:13:59.350 align:middle line:84%
Around here there's
a lot of vata energy.

00:13:59.350 --> 00:14:03.160 align:middle line:84%
And what I notice is going into
the vata mode with another vata

00:14:03.160 --> 00:14:07.670 align:middle line:84%
is a very manic kind of
experience that is so fun.

00:14:07.670 --> 00:14:10.970 align:middle line:84%
It has to be why people who
suffer from manic depressive

00:14:10.970 --> 00:14:13.106 align:middle line:84%
behavior don't want
to go on their meds.

00:14:13.106 --> 00:14:13.980 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: Absolutely.

00:14:13.980 --> 00:14:16.560 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Because you're
just flying with ideas,

00:14:16.560 --> 00:14:18.800 align:middle line:90%
rapid-fire creativity and such.

00:14:18.800 --> 00:14:21.730 align:middle line:84%
But oftentimes I notice that
at the end of those sessions we

00:14:21.730 --> 00:14:25.130 align:middle line:84%
create, create, create,
it's so fun, but sometimes

00:14:25.130 --> 00:14:27.310 align:middle line:90%
not much comes of it.

00:14:27.310 --> 00:14:28.830 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: And
that's very common.

00:14:28.830 --> 00:14:30.750 align:middle line:84%
So vatas kind of dabble
in a lot of things,

00:14:30.750 --> 00:14:32.450 align:middle line:84%
but they might not
finish anything.

00:14:32.450 --> 00:14:33.330 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:14:33.330 --> 00:14:36.370 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: There's a hard time
getting to that finish line

00:14:36.370 --> 00:14:37.840 align:middle line:90%
sometimes.

00:14:37.840 --> 00:14:40.800 align:middle line:84%
Also vata people are
very creative people.

00:14:40.800 --> 00:14:44.440 align:middle line:84%
So if we were to look at
stereotypical vata people,

00:14:44.440 --> 00:14:46.340 align:middle line:84%
you might look at Vincent
van Gogh or someone

00:14:46.340 --> 00:14:50.560 align:middle line:84%
like that, extraordinarily
creative, very productive,

00:14:50.560 --> 00:14:54.470 align:middle line:84%
but mentally just
had a very hard time

00:14:54.470 --> 00:14:57.160 align:middle line:84%
being in this world,
the material world,

00:14:57.160 --> 00:14:58.520 align:middle line:90%
taking care of himself.

00:14:58.520 --> 00:15:02.300 align:middle line:84%
And so vatas sometimes have a
hard time being grounded, just

00:15:02.300 --> 00:15:04.220 align:middle line:84%
taking care of
their daily needs.

00:15:04.220 --> 00:15:06.470 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So when you see
people exhibiting, say,

00:15:06.470 --> 00:15:10.830 align:middle line:84%
manic depressive behavior, would
that be maybe more associated

00:15:10.830 --> 00:15:12.200 align:middle line:90%
with one dosha or another?

00:15:12.200 --> 00:15:16.580 align:middle line:84%
Would that be maybe
more common among vatas?

00:15:16.580 --> 00:15:18.170 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: It can be, definitely.

00:15:18.170 --> 00:15:20.700 align:middle line:84%
So anything that has to
do with the nervous system

00:15:20.700 --> 00:15:22.220 align:middle line:90%
is controlled by vata.

00:15:22.220 --> 00:15:25.240 align:middle line:84%
Anything that's
rapidly changing is

00:15:25.240 --> 00:15:26.800 align:middle line:90%
going to be controlled by vata.

00:15:26.800 --> 00:15:30.010 align:middle line:84%
So absolutely when you're going
up and down, up and down very

00:15:30.010 --> 00:15:34.230 align:middle line:84%
rapidly, that is a
vata type of condition.

00:15:34.230 --> 00:15:34.950 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: OK.

00:15:34.950 --> 00:15:38.300 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: There might be
some other doshas involved.

00:15:38.300 --> 00:15:41.450 align:middle line:84%
And you have to remember that
everybody has all three doshas,

00:15:41.450 --> 00:15:45.010 align:middle line:84%
so we're a unique percentage
of all three doshas.

00:15:45.010 --> 00:15:47.390 align:middle line:84%
And so somebody might
have a lot of vata

00:15:47.390 --> 00:15:49.470 align:middle line:84%
and less of the
other two or a lot

00:15:49.470 --> 00:15:51.740 align:middle line:84%
of pitta, which is
the second dosha,

00:15:51.740 --> 00:15:54.860 align:middle line:84%
or a lot of kapha, which is the
third and less of the others.

00:15:54.860 --> 00:15:56.480 align:middle line:90%
Or they might be dual doshic.

00:15:56.480 --> 00:15:59.620 align:middle line:84%
They might have a lot of vata
and pitta at the same time.

00:15:59.620 --> 00:16:02.440 align:middle line:84%
So there's a lot of variation
within this where we're

00:16:02.440 --> 00:16:04.250 align:middle line:84%
going to simplify
today for people.

00:16:04.250 --> 00:16:05.080 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: OK, yes.

00:16:05.080 --> 00:16:06.170 align:middle line:90%
Just keeping it simple.

00:16:06.170 --> 00:16:06.370 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: Yeah.

00:16:06.370 --> 00:16:06.953 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: OK.

00:16:06.953 --> 00:16:09.170 align:middle line:84%
So then we need
to go on to pitta.

00:16:09.170 --> 00:16:11.700 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: So pitta people
tend to have a lot of heat

00:16:11.700 --> 00:16:13.160 align:middle line:90%
in their body.

00:16:13.160 --> 00:16:16.730 align:middle line:84%
Pitta is the biochemical
energy system of the body.

00:16:16.730 --> 00:16:20.090 align:middle line:84%
It has to do with
neurotransmitters and hormones

00:16:20.090 --> 00:16:21.280 align:middle line:90%
and enzymes.

00:16:21.280 --> 00:16:24.150 align:middle line:84%
It's that biological
principle that

00:16:24.150 --> 00:16:28.570 align:middle line:84%
has to do with transformation,
assimilation, digestion.

00:16:28.570 --> 00:16:31.980 align:middle line:84%
So it has to do
with, in some degree,

00:16:31.980 --> 00:16:35.280 align:middle line:84%
our cellular intelligence, the
intelligence within the body.

00:16:35.280 --> 00:16:37.720 align:middle line:84%
So pitta people tend to
be very bright people.

00:16:37.720 --> 00:16:38.970 align:middle line:90%
They learn things very well.

00:16:38.970 --> 00:16:40.250 align:middle line:90%
They get things quickly.

00:16:40.250 --> 00:16:43.210 align:middle line:84%
They're organized,
get-things-done type of people.

00:16:43.210 --> 00:16:47.860 align:middle line:84%
They can be very Type
A, goal-oriented people,

00:16:47.860 --> 00:16:50.810 align:middle line:84%
go-getters, high achievers,
that kind of thing.

00:16:50.810 --> 00:16:52.850 align:middle line:84%
When pitta goes
out of balance, it

00:16:52.850 --> 00:16:56.640 align:middle line:84%
tends to get into
a situation of what

00:16:56.640 --> 00:16:59.070 align:middle line:84%
we call too much heat
in the body, what

00:16:59.070 --> 00:17:02.670 align:middle line:84%
Western medicine might
call inflammation.

00:17:02.670 --> 00:17:04.869 align:middle line:84%
So pittas are very,
very likely to go

00:17:04.869 --> 00:17:07.290 align:middle line:84%
into inflammatory
types of diseases

00:17:07.290 --> 00:17:09.390 align:middle line:90%
or infectious types of diseases.

00:17:09.390 --> 00:17:10.755 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: A lot of the -itises.

00:17:10.755 --> 00:17:12.630 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: A lot of the
-itises, so sinusitus.

00:17:12.630 --> 00:17:15.299 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Like colitis,
arthritis, all of them.

00:17:15.299 --> 00:17:16.215 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: All of them.

00:17:16.215 --> 00:17:19.300 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And those are all
basically inflammation-based.

00:17:19.300 --> 00:17:21.690 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: Inflammation
or infection-based,

00:17:21.690 --> 00:17:25.109 align:middle line:84%
a lot of inflammation and
infection-based based diseases.

00:17:25.109 --> 00:17:27.220 align:middle line:84%
Digestively, they tend
to be the ones that

00:17:27.220 --> 00:17:33.390 align:middle line:84%
get the burning sensations,
the gastritis, heartburn,

00:17:33.390 --> 00:17:36.310 align:middle line:84%
peptic ulcers, that
kind of thing, diarrhea.

00:17:36.310 --> 00:17:39.650 align:middle line:84%
They're more likely to get
diarrhea, burning diarrhea,

00:17:39.650 --> 00:17:41.880 align:middle line:84%
bloody diarrhea,
that kind of thing,

00:17:41.880 --> 00:17:43.620 align:middle line:90%
where there's a lot of heat.

00:17:43.620 --> 00:17:47.360 align:middle line:84%
We would say energetically
that those types of issues

00:17:47.360 --> 00:17:49.440 align:middle line:84%
have a lot of heat
involved in them.

00:17:49.440 --> 00:17:52.880 align:middle line:84%
Red things, rashes,
all kinds of hives

00:17:52.880 --> 00:17:58.480 align:middle line:84%
and urticaria and red
rashy kinds of-- those

00:17:58.480 --> 00:18:00.900 align:middle line:84%
are very, very common
for pitta people.

00:18:00.900 --> 00:18:03.510 align:middle line:84%
So mentally/emotionally
when they're in balance,

00:18:03.510 --> 00:18:05.400 align:middle line:90%
pitta people are really bright.

00:18:05.400 --> 00:18:07.290 align:middle line:84%
They can learn
things very quickly.

00:18:07.290 --> 00:18:08.040 align:middle line:90%
They get things.

00:18:08.040 --> 00:18:09.490 align:middle line:90%
They can be really organized.

00:18:09.490 --> 00:18:12.460 align:middle line:84%
But when that heat starts
to build up in their system,

00:18:12.460 --> 00:18:15.264 align:middle line:84%
mentally and emotionally they
go into anger and frustration--

00:18:15.264 --> 00:18:16.180 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Impatience.

00:18:16.180 --> 00:18:19.150 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: --irritability,
impatience.

00:18:19.150 --> 00:18:23.380 align:middle line:10%
So you would get that very
quick temper, short temper.

00:18:23.380 --> 00:18:25.030 align:middle line:10%
That would be a pitta person.

00:18:25.030 --> 00:18:27.200 align:middle line:10%
And then they have very
high goals and standards

00:18:27.200 --> 00:18:28.116 align:middle line:10%
for themselves.

00:18:28.116 --> 00:18:30.240 align:middle line:10%
And when they don't meet
those goals and standards,

00:18:30.240 --> 00:18:33.212 align:middle line:10%
they get very self-judgmental
and self-critical.

00:18:33.212 --> 00:18:35.170 align:middle line:10%
So they can be very hard
on themselves as well.

