00:27:15.719 --> 00:27:18.260 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: A lot of reassurance
that they're not going to gain

00:27:18.260 --> 00:27:21.020 align:middle line:90%
excessive amounts of weight.

00:27:21.020 --> 00:27:23.670 align:middle line:84%
I really think it's
about the relationship

00:27:23.670 --> 00:27:26.410 align:middle line:84%
that you start to
have with the person.

00:27:26.410 --> 00:27:29.320 align:middle line:84%
So in the beginning, you have
to foster that relationship.

00:27:29.320 --> 00:27:30.540 align:middle line:90%
There has to be some trust.

00:27:30.540 --> 00:27:32.540 align:middle line:90%
It's the art of medicine.

00:27:32.540 --> 00:27:36.510 align:middle line:84%
And then when they start to
follow the guidelines, when

00:27:36.510 --> 00:27:38.372 align:middle line:84%
they start to do the
little baby steps

00:27:38.372 --> 00:27:40.080 align:middle line:84%
and try some of these
things out and they

00:27:40.080 --> 00:27:42.970 align:middle line:84%
see that it's working for them
and they're feeling better,

00:27:42.970 --> 00:27:45.031 align:middle line:84%
that's when they're
going to have more trust.

00:27:45.031 --> 00:27:47.530 align:middle line:84%
And they're going to come back
and go, OK, well, that really

00:27:47.530 --> 00:27:48.770 align:middle line:90%
worked for me.

00:27:48.770 --> 00:27:50.310 align:middle line:84%
And they're willing
to do more then.

00:27:50.310 --> 00:27:53.580 align:middle line:10%
And so it's little steps that
you have to take sometimes

00:27:53.580 --> 00:27:56.140 align:middle line:10%
with people, especially
when culturally they're

00:27:56.140 --> 00:27:58.524 align:middle line:10%
being given all
the wrong messages.

00:27:58.524 --> 00:27:59.440 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Absolutely.

00:27:59.440 --> 00:28:02.430 align:middle line:84%
And it has to be very
difficult also for vatas,

00:28:02.430 --> 00:28:05.725 align:middle line:84%
who are essentially going out
of balance because of the way

00:28:05.725 --> 00:28:07.100 align:middle line:84%
they're treating
their body, even

00:28:07.100 --> 00:28:08.683 align:middle line:84%
though they think
it's very healthful.

00:28:08.683 --> 00:28:11.660 align:middle line:84%
And we're going to get to
that in a moment, the care

00:28:11.660 --> 00:28:13.309 align:middle line:84%
and feeding manual
for these doshas.

00:28:13.309 --> 00:28:13.850 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: OK.

00:28:13.850 --> 00:28:16.183 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: But first I would
like to talk about the fact

00:28:16.183 --> 00:28:20.510 align:middle line:84%
that you use some very classical
forms of diagnosis when people

00:28:20.510 --> 00:28:21.950 align:middle line:90%
come into your office.

00:28:21.950 --> 00:28:24.460 align:middle line:84%
And so just so people can
kind of look in the mirror

00:28:24.460 --> 00:28:26.480 align:middle line:84%
and get a glimpse of
themselves in this part

00:28:26.480 --> 00:28:30.360 align:middle line:84%
of the conversation, let's talk
about the face and the nail

00:28:30.360 --> 00:28:31.519 align:middle line:90%
and tongue diagnosis.

00:28:31.519 --> 00:28:32.060 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: OK.

00:28:32.060 --> 00:28:33.620 align:middle line:84%
So when somebody
comes to see me,

00:28:33.620 --> 00:28:36.890 align:middle line:84%
after their thorough
history-- I take a much more

00:28:36.890 --> 00:28:40.050 align:middle line:84%
thorough history than most
medical doctors would--

00:28:40.050 --> 00:28:41.420 align:middle line:90%
then I look at their faces.

00:28:41.420 --> 00:28:43.490 align:middle line:84%
In Ayurveda we have
face diagnosis,

00:28:43.490 --> 00:28:45.870 align:middle line:84%
so we can tell various
things from the face.

00:28:45.870 --> 00:28:48.500 align:middle line:84%
So I'll give you just
one little small example.

00:28:48.500 --> 00:28:51.240 align:middle line:84%
A lot of people will have
dark circles under their eyes,

00:28:51.240 --> 00:28:55.125 align:middle line:84%
and we say that that can
relate to the adrenal glands.

00:28:55.125 --> 00:28:57.130 align:middle line:90%
It can relate to the vata dosha.

00:28:57.130 --> 00:29:02.190 align:middle line:84%
So what Western medicine
calls severe adrenal fatigue

00:29:02.190 --> 00:29:05.230 align:middle line:84%
we might call a vata
type of disorder.

00:29:05.230 --> 00:29:06.810 align:middle line:84%
So you might see
that with someone

00:29:06.810 --> 00:29:09.300 align:middle line:90%
who has a vata type of disorder.

00:29:09.300 --> 00:29:10.870 align:middle line:90%
You might see really dry lips.

00:29:10.870 --> 00:29:13.530 align:middle line:84%
We see that a lot in Colorado,
where people have really,

00:29:13.530 --> 00:29:16.240 align:middle line:90%
really dry, cracked lips.

00:29:16.240 --> 00:29:18.740 align:middle line:84%
And we say that kind of
reflects to the colon.

00:29:18.740 --> 00:29:21.749 align:middle line:84%
And so that means that person's
colon is really dry as well.

00:29:21.749 --> 00:29:23.540 align:middle line:84%
So in that way, we can
tell a lot of things

00:29:23.540 --> 00:29:25.160 align:middle line:90%
from looking at their face.

00:29:25.160 --> 00:29:29.410 align:middle line:84%
Then usually I move
on to their tongue.

00:29:29.410 --> 00:29:33.930 align:middle line:10%
You have an entire picture
of your intestinal--

00:29:33.930 --> 00:29:36.030 align:middle line:10%
not just intestinal,
but your entire organ

00:29:36.030 --> 00:29:37.792 align:middle line:10%
system on your tongue.

00:29:37.792 --> 00:29:39.750 align:middle line:10%
>> REGINA: Kind of like
the hands and the feet.

00:29:39.750 --> 00:29:40.530 align:middle line:10%
>> DESAI: Mm hmm.

00:29:40.530 --> 00:29:41.196 align:middle line:10%
>> REGINA: Yeah.

00:29:41.196 --> 00:29:46.100 align:middle line:10%
>> DESAI: It's like a little
map of the entire body reflected

00:29:46.100 --> 00:29:47.010 align:middle line:10%
on the tongue.

00:29:47.010 --> 00:29:49.450 align:middle line:10%
So by looking at your tongue,
we can tell different things

00:29:49.450 --> 00:29:51.250 align:middle line:10%
about different organ systems.

00:29:51.250 --> 00:29:53.700 align:middle line:90%
We can tell about toxins.

00:29:53.700 --> 00:29:58.420 align:middle line:84%
When we see people
having some sort

00:29:58.420 --> 00:30:00.919 align:middle line:84%
of white discharge or
something on their tongue--

00:30:00.919 --> 00:30:02.210 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Fuzzy white tongues.

00:30:02.210 --> 00:30:04.880 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: --fuzzy white tongues,
we would say that those are

00:30:04.880 --> 00:30:05.960 align:middle line:90%
toxins on the tongue.

00:30:05.960 --> 00:30:08.580 align:middle line:84%
We like to see a nice
clean, pink tongue.

00:30:08.580 --> 00:30:11.240 align:middle line:84%
So when people have either
white or sometimes you'll

00:30:11.240 --> 00:30:15.080 align:middle line:84%
see a yellowish coating on
the tongue, all of those

00:30:15.080 --> 00:30:16.160 align:middle line:90%
tend to be toxins.

00:30:16.160 --> 00:30:20.190 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes there tend to be
more of one area than another,

00:30:20.190 --> 00:30:22.470 align:middle line:84%
so we can even tell
where the toxins are.

00:30:22.470 --> 00:30:24.760 align:middle line:90%
We look at teeth marks.

00:30:24.760 --> 00:30:27.084 align:middle line:84%
We say that is a sign
of malabsorption.

00:30:27.084 --> 00:30:28.000 align:middle line:90%
And there's actually--

00:30:28.000 --> 00:30:29.916 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: What do you
mean teeth marks, then?

00:30:29.916 --> 00:30:32.260 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: So sometimes if
you take a look in the mirror

00:30:32.260 --> 00:30:34.440 align:middle line:84%
and stick your tongue out,
you'll see that you have little

00:30:34.440 --> 00:30:36.180 align:middle line:84%
teeth marks on the
sides of your tongue.

00:30:36.180 --> 00:30:37.040 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Little impressions.

00:30:37.040 --> 00:30:38.248 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: Little impressions.

00:30:38.248 --> 00:30:41.200 align:middle line:84%
And those are because, from
an Ayurvedic point of view,

00:30:41.200 --> 00:30:43.870 align:middle line:84%
we say you're just not
absorbing nutrients very well.

00:30:43.870 --> 00:30:46.060 align:middle line:84%
There's some
malabsorption going on.

00:30:46.060 --> 00:30:50.030 align:middle line:84%
From a Western point of view,
we know that those are rapidly

00:30:50.030 --> 00:30:53.470 align:middle line:84%
dividing tissues, because
they're constantly

00:30:53.470 --> 00:30:56.616 align:middle line:84%
getting irritated by your
teeth and eating and chewing

00:30:56.616 --> 00:30:57.990 align:middle line:84%
and everything
that you're doing.

00:30:57.990 --> 00:31:00.550 align:middle line:84%
So those tissues on the
sides of your tongue

00:31:00.550 --> 00:31:03.060 align:middle line:84%
have to be dividing
very, very rapidly.

00:31:03.060 --> 00:31:06.220 align:middle line:84%
And when you don't have
enough micronutrients--

00:31:06.220 --> 00:31:09.930 align:middle line:84%
you might call those
minerals, vitamins,

00:31:09.930 --> 00:31:13.140 align:middle line:84%
cofactors-- then you're not
going to be able to divide

00:31:13.140 --> 00:31:17.237 align:middle line:84%
and keep up with that rapid rate
of cell division that you need.

00:31:17.237 --> 00:31:19.070 align:middle line:84%
And so then you end up
with the teeth marks.

00:31:19.070 --> 00:31:21.560 align:middle line:84%
So from even a scientific
Western point of view,

00:31:21.560 --> 00:31:23.470 align:middle line:84%
you can see why
that would happen.

00:31:23.470 --> 00:31:25.270 align:middle line:84%
Somebody who has
plenty of nutrients

00:31:25.270 --> 00:31:27.930 align:middle line:84%
is not going to get the teeth
marks as easily as somebody

00:31:27.930 --> 00:31:30.000 align:middle line:84%
who doesn't have enough
of those micronutrients.

00:31:30.000 --> 00:31:32.210 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Now what about
some of the other factors,

00:31:32.210 --> 00:31:35.900 align:middle line:84%
such as deep creases or-- what
is it called?-- geological--

00:31:35.900 --> 00:31:36.780 align:middle line:90%
what is the name?

00:31:36.780 --> 00:31:37.550 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: A geographic tongue.

00:31:37.550 --> 00:31:39.050 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Geographic
tongue, yes.

00:31:39.050 --> 00:31:42.400 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: So we say a geographic
tongue is a severe vata type

00:31:42.400 --> 00:31:45.280 align:middle line:84%
of disorder, people who
have really deep-seated vata

00:31:45.280 --> 00:31:46.020 align:middle line:90%
in their body.

00:31:46.020 --> 00:31:47.110 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: It means
it looks like a map.

00:31:47.110 --> 00:31:47.690 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: It looks like a map.

00:31:47.690 --> 00:31:48.190 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: So many crevices.

00:31:48.190 --> 00:31:50.065 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: They have lots
of crevices all over

00:31:50.065 --> 00:31:50.950 align:middle line:90%
their tongues.

00:31:50.950 --> 00:31:52.950 align:middle line:10%
Some people will have
just a crevice down

00:31:52.950 --> 00:31:55.130 align:middle line:10%
the middle of their
tongue, and sometimes it'll

00:31:55.130 --> 00:31:57.290 align:middle line:10%
be more in the front
of their tongue.

00:31:57.290 --> 00:31:59.530 align:middle line:10%
And we say that correlates
more with the neck

00:31:59.530 --> 00:32:00.390 align:middle line:10%
and the upper back.

00:32:00.390 --> 00:32:02.570 align:middle line:10%
And they might have neck
or upper back stress

00:32:02.570 --> 00:32:05.430 align:middle line:10%
or tension or even pain.

00:32:05.430 --> 00:32:07.630 align:middle line:10%
Sometimes it'll be more in
the middle of the tongue,

00:32:07.630 --> 00:32:09.700 align:middle line:10%
and that correlates
to the mid-back.

00:32:09.700 --> 00:32:12.270 align:middle line:10%
Or it'll be in very
back of the tongue

00:32:12.270 --> 00:32:14.170 align:middle line:10%
where they have a
very deep crease,

00:32:14.170 --> 00:32:16.930 align:middle line:10%
and that usually
correlates to either a lot

00:32:16.930 --> 00:32:19.730 align:middle line:10%
of stress and tension in
the lower back or some kind

00:32:19.730 --> 00:32:22.452 align:middle line:10%
of physical lower back issue.

00:32:22.452 --> 00:32:24.410 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And when it's
just creases all over,

00:32:24.410 --> 00:32:26.285 align:middle line:84%
that mean just a
very dry condition,

00:32:26.285 --> 00:32:27.580 align:middle line:90%
a very vata condition.

00:32:27.580 --> 00:32:28.697 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: Very vata, yes.

00:32:28.697 --> 00:32:29.280 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: OK.

00:32:29.280 --> 00:32:33.190 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: The vata dosha has
been disturbed for a very long

00:32:33.190 --> 00:32:35.900 align:middle line:84%
period of time in that
person and might be in some

00:32:35.900 --> 00:32:37.126 align:middle line:90%
of the deeper tissue layers.

00:32:37.126 --> 00:32:39.000 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And this is
probably a no-brainer,

00:32:39.000 --> 00:32:42.099 align:middle line:84%
but when someone has a
swollen, fiery red tongue--

00:32:42.099 --> 00:32:43.890 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: That's going
to be a lot of heat.

00:32:43.890 --> 00:32:44.320 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:32:44.320 --> 00:32:45.220 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: A lot of
heat in the body.

00:32:45.220 --> 00:32:47.553 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: A lot of pitta
that needs to be balanced out.

00:32:47.553 --> 00:32:50.060 align:middle line:84%
And finally, on that note,
I've seen some of the books

00:32:50.060 --> 00:32:53.800 align:middle line:84%
on Chinese tongue diagnosis,
which are just shocking,

00:32:53.800 --> 00:32:56.790 align:middle line:84%
to think that, A, someone
might not notice some

00:32:56.790 --> 00:32:58.770 align:middle line:84%
of these conditions
on their own tongue

00:32:58.770 --> 00:33:00.500 align:middle line:84%
and, B, that you
could still be walking

00:33:00.500 --> 00:33:03.260 align:middle line:84%
and breathing and living
with tongues that are black

00:33:03.260 --> 00:33:06.550 align:middle line:84%
or excessively
deep golden colors

00:33:06.550 --> 00:33:08.575 align:middle line:84%
on the back of the
tongue, for example.

00:33:08.575 --> 00:33:11.350 align:middle line:90%


00:33:11.350 --> 00:33:13.340 align:middle line:84%
I don't even know
the question here.

00:33:13.340 --> 00:33:15.160 align:middle line:90%
It's so shocking.

00:33:15.160 --> 00:33:18.260 align:middle line:84%
How do people show up-- Have you
seen some of these conditions?

00:33:18.260 --> 00:33:21.550 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: Well, I think a lot of
times in the West we're really

00:33:21.550 --> 00:33:24.680 align:middle line:84%
not focused on our
own physical bodies,

00:33:24.680 --> 00:33:27.140 align:middle line:84%
and so we don't have a lot
of body awareness or body

00:33:27.140 --> 00:33:28.500 align:middle line:90%
consciousness.

00:33:28.500 --> 00:33:31.570 align:middle line:84%
And so many people in the
West can be walking around,

00:33:31.570 --> 00:33:35.070 align:middle line:84%
and they really don't have any
sense of what their tongue even

00:33:35.070 --> 00:33:37.260 align:middle line:84%
looks like because
we don't really

00:33:37.260 --> 00:33:39.880 align:middle line:84%
think we can
self-diagnose ourselves.

00:33:39.880 --> 00:33:42.010 align:middle line:84%
We don't think we
can heal ourselves.

00:33:42.010 --> 00:33:44.930 align:middle line:84%
And Ayurveda's the
science of self-healing.

00:33:44.930 --> 00:33:46.410 align:middle line:90%
It's very empowering.

00:33:46.410 --> 00:33:47.654 align:middle line:90%
So we say, yes, you can.

00:33:47.654 --> 00:33:48.820 align:middle line:90%
You can look at your tongue.

00:33:48.820 --> 00:33:50.720 align:middle line:90%
You can look at your face.

00:33:50.720 --> 00:33:52.220 align:middle line:84%
There's many things
you can look at.

00:33:52.220 --> 00:33:55.090 align:middle line:84%
And you can actually kind
of get an idea of as to

00:33:55.090 --> 00:33:56.820 align:middle line:90%
what's going on your own body.

00:33:56.820 --> 00:33:58.800 align:middle line:84%
And then with a little
bit of guidance,

00:33:58.800 --> 00:34:01.030 align:middle line:84%
you can sort of
move yourself away

00:34:01.030 --> 00:34:03.170 align:middle line:90%
from that to better health.

00:34:03.170 --> 00:34:05.369 align:middle line:90%
So I think some of it is just--

00:34:05.369 --> 00:34:06.660 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: A lack of awareness.

00:34:06.660 --> 00:34:07.880 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: --a lack
of awareness, yes.

00:34:07.880 --> 00:34:09.469 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Now one thing women
are more aware of in this

00:34:09.469 --> 00:34:10.844 align:middle line:84%
culture than men
are their nails.

00:34:10.844 --> 00:34:12.300 align:middle line:90%
And you do nail diagnosis.

00:34:12.300 --> 00:34:12.510 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: I do.

00:34:12.510 --> 00:34:13.820 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: This is
part of it as well.

00:34:13.820 --> 00:34:15.739 align:middle line:84%
Let's talk about some
of the chief factors

00:34:15.739 --> 00:34:19.820 align:middle line:84%
that people might see,
like splitting nails

00:34:19.820 --> 00:34:23.780 align:middle line:84%
or horizontal or
vertical types of ridges.

00:34:23.780 --> 00:34:26.790 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: So a lot of times
we'll see vertical ridges

00:34:26.790 --> 00:34:28.020 align:middle line:90%
on people's nails.

00:34:28.020 --> 00:34:31.090 align:middle line:84%
That's very similar to the
little ridges on your tongue.

00:34:31.090 --> 00:34:33.949 align:middle line:84%
It tends to correlate with
malabsorption, just not

00:34:33.949 --> 00:34:35.801 align:middle line:90%
absorbing nutrients very well.

00:34:35.801 --> 00:34:36.800 align:middle line:90%
And it's the same thing.

00:34:36.800 --> 00:34:39.050 align:middle line:10%
You have the back of your nail.

00:34:39.050 --> 00:34:41.929 align:middle line:10%
You're rapidly dividing those
tissues to grow your nail.

00:34:41.929 --> 00:34:43.590 align:middle line:10%
And if you don't
have any nutrition,

00:34:43.590 --> 00:34:47.139 align:middle line:10%
it's going to come out as a
vertical kind of a scar almost.

00:34:47.139 --> 00:34:52.460 align:middle line:10%
And so the more
vertical fissures--

00:34:52.460 --> 00:34:55.400 align:middle line:10%
I don't know what you want
to call them-- we might say

00:34:55.400 --> 00:34:56.760 align:middle line:10%
are from malabsorption.

00:34:56.760 --> 00:34:58.554 align:middle line:10%
When they're more horizontal--

00:34:58.554 --> 00:34:59.220 align:middle line:10%
>> REGINA: Yeah.

00:34:59.220 --> 00:35:00.350 align:middle line:90%
Like the speed bumps.

00:35:00.350 --> 00:35:01.830 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: --like
the speed bumps,

00:35:01.830 --> 00:35:03.740 align:middle line:84%
then we would say
that's more metabolic.

00:35:03.740 --> 00:35:05.535 align:middle line:84%
Something's happening
with the person

00:35:05.535 --> 00:35:06.827 align:middle line:90%
from a metabolic point of view.

00:35:06.827 --> 00:35:09.035 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So you're seeing
a metabolic cycle, maybe,

00:35:09.035 --> 00:35:11.170 align:middle line:84%
where something happened,
something a little more

00:35:11.170 --> 00:35:13.120 align:middle line:84%
traumatic may have happened,
and then it healed up.

00:35:13.120 --> 00:35:14.370 align:middle line:90%
But could it be, like, cyclical?

00:35:14.370 --> 00:35:15.203 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: You might.

00:35:15.203 --> 00:35:18.130 align:middle line:84%
Or they're more
horizontal ridges, really.

00:35:18.130 --> 00:35:20.380 align:middle line:84%
And it could be
cyclical, or it could

00:35:20.380 --> 00:35:23.960 align:middle line:84%
be something that's happening
right now metabolically

00:35:23.960 --> 00:35:26.080 align:middle line:84%
where they're just not
able to keep up with it.

00:35:26.080 --> 00:35:27.550 align:middle line:84%
And you'll see that
in their nails.

00:35:27.550 --> 00:35:30.030 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And really thin,
papery nails that just kind

00:35:30.030 --> 00:35:30.529 align:middle line:90%
of peel?

00:35:30.529 --> 00:35:32.580 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: A lot of vata.

00:35:32.580 --> 00:35:35.530 align:middle line:90%
Lack of minerals, a lot of vata.

00:35:35.530 --> 00:35:39.740 align:middle line:84%
And then sometimes we'll see
little spots, white spots

00:35:39.740 --> 00:35:40.400 align:middle line:90%
on the nails.

00:35:40.400 --> 00:35:43.830 align:middle line:84%
And we say that is also a
mineral deficiency in the body.

00:35:43.830 --> 00:35:47.140 align:middle line:84%
And so again, going back
to that micronutrients

00:35:47.140 --> 00:35:50.750 align:middle line:84%
needed for-- if you
hit your nail bed,

00:35:50.750 --> 00:35:52.810 align:middle line:84%
you might scar that
nail bed, and you

00:35:52.810 --> 00:35:56.140 align:middle line:84%
might have that little white
scar that slowly grows out.

00:35:56.140 --> 00:35:58.440 align:middle line:84%
And because you weren't
able to heal that,

00:35:58.440 --> 00:36:00.510 align:middle line:84%
there's a good chance
the reason you wouldn't

00:36:00.510 --> 00:36:01.968 align:middle line:84%
be able to heal
that is because you

00:36:01.968 --> 00:36:03.810 align:middle line:84%
didn't have enough
micronutrients.

00:36:03.810 --> 00:36:07.750 align:middle line:84%
And so we say when you have
a lot of those, most likely

00:36:07.750 --> 00:36:10.050 align:middle line:84%
you're having some sort
of malabsorption problem

00:36:10.050 --> 00:36:12.890 align:middle line:84%
and a mineral
deficiency of some sort.

00:36:12.890 --> 00:36:16.322 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So that can happen,
I assume, to any of the doshas,

00:36:16.322 --> 00:36:18.280 align:middle line:84%
where you can end up with
malabsorption issues.

00:36:18.280 --> 00:36:20.420 align:middle line:84%
So because this is
showing up in nails,

00:36:20.420 --> 00:36:21.860 align:middle line:84%
it'll be showing
up on the tongue.

00:36:21.860 --> 00:36:23.318 align:middle line:84%
What is one of the
first things you

00:36:23.318 --> 00:36:25.190 align:middle line:84%
have people do if
they're not absorbing.

00:36:25.190 --> 00:36:29.502 align:middle line:84%
Is it a process of detoxing
before you can absorb?

00:36:29.502 --> 00:36:31.210 align:middle line:84%
What are some of the
Ayurvedic processes?

00:36:31.210 --> 00:36:34.840 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: Each person is so
unique that there's no one set

00:36:34.840 --> 00:36:37.030 align:middle line:84%
way that I might
proceed with someone.

00:36:37.030 --> 00:36:41.590 align:middle line:84%
But really a lot of it has to
do with what are they eating.

00:36:41.590 --> 00:36:43.290 align:middle line:84%
A lot of times people
are eating food

00:36:43.290 --> 00:36:46.060 align:middle line:84%
that they just have
no ability to digest.

00:36:46.060 --> 00:36:49.250 align:middle line:84%
So depending on what's going
on, what their doshas are,

00:36:49.250 --> 00:36:50.850 align:middle line:84%
we might start by
just putting them

00:36:50.850 --> 00:36:54.520 align:middle line:84%
on a diet that is going
to suit their ability.

00:36:54.520 --> 00:36:57.702 align:middle line:84%
We say you should eat according
to your ability to digest.

00:36:57.702 --> 00:36:58.660 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Makes sense.

00:36:58.660 --> 00:37:00.743 align:middle line:10%
>> DESAI: If you have a
very weak digestive system

00:37:00.743 --> 00:37:03.460 align:middle line:10%
and you've come to see me and
digestion's your main issue

00:37:03.460 --> 00:37:05.720 align:middle line:10%
and your digestion
is incredibly weak,

00:37:05.720 --> 00:37:09.620 align:middle line:10%
then we're going to put you
on an extremely easy to digest

00:37:09.620 --> 00:37:10.640 align:middle line:10%
diet.

00:37:10.640 --> 00:37:12.400 align:middle line:84%
So we're going to
really take the burden

00:37:12.400 --> 00:37:14.730 align:middle line:84%
off the digestive
system, let it rest.

00:37:14.730 --> 00:37:18.720 align:middle line:84%
And we really believe that
the organs of digestion

00:37:18.720 --> 00:37:21.180 align:middle line:84%
can regenerate and
heal themselves.

00:37:21.180 --> 00:37:24.180 align:middle line:84%
So we might use some herbs
and some herbal teas,

00:37:24.180 --> 00:37:25.560 align:middle line:90%
things like that to help.

00:37:25.560 --> 00:37:28.120 align:middle line:84%
But a lot of what we
would do would be diet.

00:37:28.120 --> 00:37:30.140 align:middle line:84%
We might do some
lifestyle things.

00:37:30.140 --> 00:37:32.120 align:middle line:84%
And then there might
be some detoxification

00:37:32.120 --> 00:37:33.500 align:middle line:90%
in there as well.

00:37:33.500 --> 00:37:35.910 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Well, that gets
us to the doshas again,

00:37:35.910 --> 00:37:39.839 align:middle line:84%
talking about how we feed
and care for our doshas--

00:37:39.839 --> 00:37:40.380 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: OK.

00:37:40.380 --> 00:37:42.005 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: --and the
diet specifically.

00:37:42.005 --> 00:37:44.840 align:middle line:90%


00:37:44.840 --> 00:37:48.990 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: In Ayurveda we have a
concept that opposites balance.

00:37:48.990 --> 00:37:52.280 align:middle line:84%
So each of these doshas
have certain qualities.

00:37:52.280 --> 00:37:55.160 align:middle line:90%
For example, vata's very dry.

00:37:55.160 --> 00:37:57.070 align:middle line:90%
It's very rough.

00:37:57.070 --> 00:37:58.960 align:middle line:84%
Vata people tend
to be very cold.

00:37:58.960 --> 00:38:03.100 align:middle line:84%
There's not a lot of
heat energy in vata.

00:38:03.100 --> 00:38:05.400 align:middle line:84%
So vata tends to be
cold, dry, rough,

00:38:05.400 --> 00:38:06.990 align:middle line:84%
some of these
types of qualities.

00:38:06.990 --> 00:38:09.690 align:middle line:84%
So the diet would be the
exact opposite of that.

00:38:09.690 --> 00:38:13.410 align:middle line:84%
We would actually say that
opposites would balance.

00:38:13.410 --> 00:38:15.610 align:middle line:90%
So for dry, we want moisture.

00:38:15.610 --> 00:38:19.400 align:middle line:10%
So a vata-pacifying diet is a
moist diet, a soupy, stewy kind

00:38:19.400 --> 00:38:20.870 align:middle line:10%
of casserole-y diet.

00:38:20.870 --> 00:38:23.430 align:middle line:10%
We would put warmth in
there, because vatas

00:38:23.430 --> 00:38:25.590 align:middle line:10%
have a lot of innate coldness.

00:38:25.590 --> 00:38:29.670 align:middle line:10%
So the diet would be warm,
warm with both warming spices

00:38:29.670 --> 00:38:31.450 align:middle line:10%
but also warm energetically.

00:38:31.450 --> 00:38:33.799 align:middle line:10%
The food that you eat
would be soupy and hot.

00:38:33.799 --> 00:38:36.340 align:middle line:10%
It wouldn't be-- you wouldn't
want to eat something right out

00:38:36.340 --> 00:38:36.870 align:middle line:10%
of the refrigerator.

00:38:36.870 --> 00:38:38.630 align:middle line:10%
>> REGINA: What about
things like salads?

00:38:38.630 --> 00:38:41.920 align:middle line:10%
Because I see a lot of vata
people eating a lot of salads

00:38:41.920 --> 00:38:43.050 align:middle line:10%
and then going to yoga.

00:38:43.050 --> 00:38:46.350 align:middle line:10%
>> DESAI: So we say that because
of the rough and dry quality

00:38:46.350 --> 00:38:50.680 align:middle line:10%
of vata, most salads actually
have a quality to them that are

00:38:50.680 --> 00:38:53.400 align:middle line:10%
rough and cold and dry.

00:38:53.400 --> 00:38:56.560 align:middle line:10%
The fiber in the vegetable
is very, very hard to digest.

00:38:56.560 --> 00:39:00.540 align:middle line:10%
So from an Ayurvedic point
of view and most Eastern

00:39:00.540 --> 00:39:03.570 align:middle line:10%
medicines really do believe
that cooking vegetables is

00:39:03.570 --> 00:39:04.610 align:middle line:10%
better for you.

00:39:04.610 --> 00:39:08.850 align:middle line:10%
So for vatas in particular,
we would do a more cooked food

00:39:08.850 --> 00:39:11.210 align:middle line:10%
diet, including the vegetables.

00:39:11.210 --> 00:39:13.710 align:middle line:84%
And we would really cook
the vegetables quite well.

00:39:13.710 --> 00:39:17.280 align:middle line:84%
So vatas, it's recommended
that they eat more soupy,

00:39:17.280 --> 00:39:19.100 align:middle line:90%
stewy kinds of foods.

00:39:19.100 --> 00:39:20.980 align:middle line:84%
You might even puree
it in the beginning

00:39:20.980 --> 00:39:24.090 align:middle line:84%
if your digestion's really
weak, because the fiber is

00:39:24.090 --> 00:39:28.016 align:middle line:84%
so hard to digest initially
when you have a weak digestive

00:39:28.016 --> 00:39:28.515 align:middle line:90%
system.

00:39:28.515 --> 00:39:29.210 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah.

00:39:29.210 --> 00:39:31.300 align:middle line:84%
The human body has some
trouble with cellulose

00:39:31.300 --> 00:39:33.250 align:middle line:84%
anyway, breaking cellulose
down, unlike cows.

00:39:33.250 --> 00:39:34.501 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: We don't only do it.

00:39:34.501 --> 00:39:35.166 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah.

00:39:35.166 --> 00:39:37.670 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: The organisms in our
body actually are what breaks

00:39:37.670 --> 00:39:39.140 align:middle line:90%
cellulose down, but we don't.

00:39:39.140 --> 00:39:40.000 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:39:40.000 --> 00:39:44.480 align:middle line:84%
What about proteins and vatas,
because of this creativity

00:39:44.480 --> 00:39:46.050 align:middle line:90%
and airy quality?

00:39:46.050 --> 00:39:50.410 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: Vatas tend to be,
because they have a lot of this

00:39:50.410 --> 00:39:52.970 align:middle line:84%
lightness in their body-- so
that was another quality I

00:39:52.970 --> 00:39:54.130 align:middle line:90%
brought out earlier.

00:39:54.130 --> 00:39:55.591 align:middle line:90%
Vatas are very light.

00:39:55.591 --> 00:39:58.090 align:middle line:84%
They have light bone structures,
and they have this tendency

00:39:58.090 --> 00:40:01.330 align:middle line:84%
to get ungrounded-- we want
to kind of ground them.

00:40:01.330 --> 00:40:03.140 align:middle line:90%
We want to pull them back down.

00:40:03.140 --> 00:40:05.420 align:middle line:84%
So heavy foods are
actually good for them.

00:40:05.420 --> 00:40:07.160 align:middle line:84%
So proteins would be
very good for them,

00:40:07.160 --> 00:40:09.710 align:middle line:84%
because proteins have a
heavy quality to them.

00:40:09.710 --> 00:40:12.940 align:middle line:84%
So vatas do really, really well
with grounding, heavy foods,

00:40:12.940 --> 00:40:14.740 align:middle line:90%
a bowl of oatmeal.

00:40:14.740 --> 00:40:17.210 align:middle line:84%
You might put a lot
of oil in the oatmeal.

00:40:17.210 --> 00:40:18.635 align:middle line:84%
So we might put
it big tablespoon

00:40:18.635 --> 00:40:20.310 align:middle line:90%
of ghee in the oatmeal.

00:40:20.310 --> 00:40:22.967 align:middle line:84%
Because, again, oils are
very, very grounding.

00:40:22.967 --> 00:40:23.550 align:middle line:90%
They're heavy.

00:40:23.550 --> 00:40:25.020 align:middle line:90%
They kind of help pull you down.

00:40:25.020 --> 00:40:26.095 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And for
those who don't know,

00:40:26.095 --> 00:40:27.220 align:middle line:90%
ghee is clarified butter.

00:40:27.220 --> 00:40:28.530 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: Ghee is
clarified butter.

00:40:28.530 --> 00:40:29.157 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:40:29.157 --> 00:40:29.740 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: Yes.

00:40:29.740 --> 00:40:33.610 align:middle line:10%
Vatas, when their digestion's
good and they can actually

00:40:33.610 --> 00:40:37.100 align:middle line:10%
digest, they would eat a
heavier kind of comfort food,

00:40:37.100 --> 00:40:40.600 align:middle line:10%
oatmeal and casseroles and
things that actually you think

00:40:40.600 --> 00:40:46.870 align:middle line:10%
of as comfort food, soft,
easy to digest, well-cooked,

00:40:46.870 --> 00:40:48.947 align:middle line:10%
but with lots of protein
and a lot of oil--

00:40:48.947 --> 00:40:50.280 align:middle line:10%
>> REGINA: A lot of oil and fat.

00:40:50.280 --> 00:40:50.625 align:middle line:10%
>> DESAI: --and fats.

00:40:50.625 --> 00:40:50.970 align:middle line:10%
Mm hmm.

00:40:50.970 --> 00:40:51.553 align:middle line:10%
>> REGINA: OK.

00:40:51.553 --> 00:40:53.760 align:middle line:84%
Now what happens when
vata goes out of balance?

00:40:53.760 --> 00:40:55.250 align:middle line:84%
Because we all
read the headlines

00:40:55.250 --> 00:40:57.760 align:middle line:84%
of highly creative
individuals who

00:40:57.760 --> 00:41:00.870 align:middle line:90%
are in rehab for the 10th time.

00:41:00.870 --> 00:41:04.050 align:middle line:84%
What is vata trying
to do when it's

00:41:04.050 --> 00:41:07.750 align:middle line:90%
self-medicating with drugs?

00:41:07.750 --> 00:41:11.240 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: Well, we say from an
Ayurvedic point of view that

00:41:11.240 --> 00:41:13.370 align:middle line:84%
when you are severely
out of balance,

00:41:13.370 --> 00:41:15.890 align:middle line:84%
when that vata energy's
so out of balance,

00:41:15.890 --> 00:41:18.360 align:middle line:84%
it almost takes on
a life of its own.

00:41:18.360 --> 00:41:21.890 align:middle line:84%
And so there's this tendency
to want to keep it alive.

00:41:21.890 --> 00:41:24.210 align:middle line:84%
So you then start
to crave things

00:41:24.210 --> 00:41:26.252 align:middle line:84%
that continue to keep
you out of balance.

00:41:26.252 --> 00:41:28.335 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So like the
manic depressive behaviors,

00:41:28.335 --> 00:41:28.770 align:middle line:90%
for example.

00:41:28.770 --> 00:41:29.519 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: Exactly.

00:41:29.519 --> 00:41:31.700 align:middle line:84%
The manics want to
be even more manic.

00:41:31.700 --> 00:41:33.740 align:middle line:84%
So the vatas want to
have even more energy.

00:41:33.740 --> 00:41:35.420 align:middle line:84%
They want to be even
more ungrounded.

00:41:35.420 --> 00:41:37.170 align:middle line:84%
They want to be
even more speedier.

00:41:37.170 --> 00:41:38.850 align:middle line:84%
So then they'll
drink a lot of coffee

00:41:38.850 --> 00:41:40.110 align:middle line:90%
or have a lot of caffeine.

00:41:40.110 --> 00:41:42.310 align:middle line:84%
And they'll kind of
speed themselves up.

00:41:42.310 --> 00:41:45.040 align:middle line:84%
And so the vata takes on
a kind of life of its own,

00:41:45.040 --> 00:41:49.030 align:middle line:84%
and it pushes you into a
lifestyle that's very unstable.

00:41:49.030 --> 00:41:51.700 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: You could end up
doing coke and a lot of other

00:41:51.700 --> 00:41:54.216 align:middle line:84%
kind of stimulating things
to keep the vata going.

00:41:54.216 --> 00:41:55.590 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: To keep
the vata going.

00:41:55.590 --> 00:41:58.150 align:middle line:84%
Because vata does control
the nervous system.

00:41:58.150 --> 00:41:59.810 align:middle line:84%
So when vata goes
out of balance,

00:41:59.810 --> 00:42:02.270 align:middle line:84%
you end up in your
sympathetic nervous system.

00:42:02.270 --> 00:42:04.332 align:middle line:84%
There is a certain
thrill to being

00:42:04.332 --> 00:42:05.790 align:middle line:84%
in your sympathetic
nervous system.

00:42:05.790 --> 00:42:07.460 align:middle line:84%
That's why we have
amusement parks.

00:42:07.460 --> 00:42:08.126 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah.

00:42:08.126 --> 00:42:09.059 align:middle line:90%
That's the gas pedal.

00:42:09.059 --> 00:42:10.350 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: That's the gas pedal.

00:42:10.350 --> 00:42:12.610 align:middle line:10%
So keeping your foot
on the gas pedal,

00:42:12.610 --> 00:42:16.010 align:middle line:10%
keeping that vata going, that
energy, it's very stimulating.

00:42:16.010 --> 00:42:19.100 align:middle line:10%
And some people, once that
vata goes out of balance,

00:42:19.100 --> 00:42:21.070 align:middle line:10%
they just can't stop.

00:42:21.070 --> 00:42:22.724 align:middle line:10%
They want-- they
continue to want that,

00:42:22.724 --> 00:42:24.890 align:middle line:10%
and so they'll just keep
their foot on the gas pedal

00:42:24.890 --> 00:42:27.190 align:middle line:10%
by whatever means
they need to use.

00:42:27.190 --> 00:42:30.020 align:middle line:10%
>> REGINA: So coffee wouldn't
necessarily be indicated

00:42:30.020 --> 00:42:33.635 align:middle line:10%
as the best morning
drink for dominant vata?

00:42:33.635 --> 00:42:34.510 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: Not really.

00:42:34.510 --> 00:42:36.175 align:middle line:90%
Because vatas are so sensitive.

00:42:36.175 --> 00:42:38.400 align:middle line:84%
They have very sensitive
nervous systems.

00:42:38.400 --> 00:42:41.620 align:middle line:84%
So anything that stimulates the
nervous system, that puts them

00:42:41.620 --> 00:42:45.220 align:middle line:84%
into their sympathetic nervous
system, their kind of fight

00:42:45.220 --> 00:42:50.540 align:middle line:84%
and flight nervous system
would be unbalancing to them.

00:42:50.540 --> 00:42:51.580 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: OK.

00:42:51.580 --> 00:42:53.970 align:middle line:10%
>> DESAI: I tell people when
they're vata never leave

00:42:53.970 --> 00:42:55.730 align:middle line:10%
the house without eating.

00:42:55.730 --> 00:42:59.240 align:middle line:10%
Or if you're in such a rush
that you can't do that,

00:42:59.240 --> 00:43:02.701 align:middle line:10%
at least have a cup of warm
water before you leave.

00:43:02.701 --> 00:43:04.950 align:middle line:10%
>> REGINA: I once had, when
I was doing a documentary,

00:43:04.950 --> 00:43:06.210 align:middle line:10%
we were out on the road.

00:43:06.210 --> 00:43:10.720 align:middle line:84%
The crew was out on the road,
and my lead cameraman was vata.

00:43:10.720 --> 00:43:11.950 align:middle line:90%
Ugh.

00:43:11.950 --> 00:43:16.800 align:middle line:84%
The entire crew had to function
around his emotional and mental

00:43:16.800 --> 00:43:18.810 align:middle line:90%
needs, which was exactly that.

00:43:18.810 --> 00:43:22.140 align:middle line:84%
Come a certain time in the
afternoon, we had to stop.

00:43:22.140 --> 00:43:23.995 align:middle line:84%
He had to have his
muffin or whatever,

00:43:23.995 --> 00:43:26.004 align:middle line:84%
or we were going to
have a miserable day.

00:43:26.004 --> 00:43:27.420 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: And
that's part of vata.

00:43:27.420 --> 00:43:29.355 align:middle line:84%
Vatas need a very
regular lifestyle.

00:43:29.355 --> 00:43:31.860 align:middle line:84%
To keep that nervous
system in balance,

00:43:31.860 --> 00:43:33.280 align:middle line:90%
you need your three meals a day.

00:43:33.280 --> 00:43:34.430 align:middle line:90%
You need your routine.

00:43:34.430 --> 00:43:36.020 align:middle line:84%
You need to wake up
at the same time,

00:43:36.020 --> 00:43:37.430 align:middle line:90%
go to bed at the same time.

00:43:37.430 --> 00:43:39.471 align:middle line:84%
When you think about it,
what you're dealing with

00:43:39.471 --> 00:43:42.020 align:middle line:84%
is a person who has a very
sensitive nervous system.

00:43:42.020 --> 00:43:46.540 align:middle line:84%
So then we have to create
an artificial cushion

00:43:46.540 --> 00:43:49.809 align:middle line:84%
around that person where
their routines, their rhythms,

00:43:49.809 --> 00:43:50.350 align:middle line:90%
their foods--

00:43:50.350 --> 00:43:51.558 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Stability matters.

00:43:51.558 --> 00:43:53.870 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: --a lot of stability
to give that person some

00:43:53.870 --> 00:43:55.550 align:middle line:90%
grounded energy.

00:43:55.550 --> 00:43:58.350 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So they might do
well in a more kapha-vata

00:43:58.350 --> 00:43:59.205 align:middle line:90%
relationship.

00:43:59.205 --> 00:44:00.080 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: They might.

00:44:00.080 --> 00:44:00.360 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: They might.

00:44:00.360 --> 00:44:02.318 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: Where somebody
remembers to feed them

00:44:02.318 --> 00:44:03.069 align:middle line:90%
regularly, yes.

00:44:03.069 --> 00:44:03.860 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Exactly.

00:44:03.860 --> 00:44:05.670 align:middle line:84%
I know a lot of
scientists and physicists

00:44:05.670 --> 00:44:09.467 align:middle line:84%
who have lovely kapha wives,
which really grounds them.

00:44:09.467 --> 00:44:10.050 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: Yes.

00:44:10.050 --> 00:44:12.210 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So now
let's talk about pitta.

00:44:12.210 --> 00:44:14.805 align:middle line:84%
How do we care for and
feed a pitta vehicle?

00:44:14.805 --> 00:44:18.010 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: The main issue with
pitta is that amazing mind

00:44:18.010 --> 00:44:21.110 align:middle line:84%
to that wants to just be so
Type A and goal-oriented.

00:44:21.110 --> 00:44:23.370 align:middle line:90%
But that overheats the body.

00:44:23.370 --> 00:44:23.870 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:44:23.870 --> 00:44:26.510 align:middle line:84%
Or just the tendency
to want to overdo,

00:44:26.510 --> 00:44:28.420 align:middle line:90%
so that overheats the body.

00:44:28.420 --> 00:44:31.470 align:middle line:84%
So pitta diets are more
energetically based,

00:44:31.470 --> 00:44:35.830 align:middle line:84%
and they're more cooling,
and not as in iced cold food

00:44:35.830 --> 00:44:37.140 align:middle line:90%
from the refrigerator.

00:44:37.140 --> 00:44:41.540 align:middle line:84%
But we say that food has
hot energy or cold energy.

00:44:41.540 --> 00:44:44.560 align:middle line:84%
So a chili pepper is
very spicy and hot,

00:44:44.560 --> 00:44:48.820 align:middle line:84%
and a cucumber is very cool,
or aloe vera gel is very cool.

00:44:48.820 --> 00:44:52.130 align:middle line:84%
Actually, cow's milk is
very cooling in nature.

00:44:52.130 --> 00:44:55.720 align:middle line:84%
So we would put pitta people
on a cooling diet, foods

00:44:55.720 --> 00:44:58.370 align:middle line:84%
that tend to cool
down the system.

00:44:58.370 --> 00:45:01.490 align:middle line:84%
So, in the middle of summer,
a watermelon smoothie

00:45:01.490 --> 00:45:03.140 align:middle line:90%
would really cool you down.

00:45:03.140 --> 00:45:04.910 align:middle line:84%
So that's something
that we might

00:45:04.910 --> 00:45:06.960 align:middle line:84%
consider giving
someone who's pitta.

00:45:06.960 --> 00:45:10.450 align:middle line:84%
Leafy greens, a lot of the
bitter leafy green vegetables

00:45:10.450 --> 00:45:12.200 align:middle line:90%
are very, very cooling.

00:45:12.200 --> 00:45:14.840 align:middle line:84%
They can eat a little
bit of raw food.

00:45:14.840 --> 00:45:17.470 align:middle line:84%
They're kind of in between
the vata and the kapha.

00:45:17.470 --> 00:45:19.990 align:middle line:84%
They're right in the middle,
so they can do a little raw.

00:45:19.990 --> 00:45:22.020 align:middle line:84%
But in general, they
still want to do somewhat

00:45:22.020 --> 00:45:23.960 align:middle line:90%
of a cooked diet.

00:45:23.960 --> 00:45:28.300 align:middle line:84%
We're not heavy on raw in
Ayurveda in all three doshas.

00:45:28.300 --> 00:45:29.099 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:45:29.099 --> 00:45:31.765 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: But the pittas can get
away with it a little bit more.

00:45:31.765 --> 00:45:33.492 align:middle line:84%
They can eat more
room temperature food.

00:45:33.492 --> 00:45:35.700 align:middle line:84%
They don't have to have all
their food hot and soupy.

00:45:35.700 --> 00:45:39.260 align:middle line:90%


00:45:39.260 --> 00:45:41.430 align:middle line:84%
The other thing that we
just never do in Ayurveda

00:45:41.430 --> 00:45:42.750 align:middle line:90%
is ice cold food.

00:45:42.750 --> 00:45:45.490 align:middle line:84%
We never do iced drinks for
any of the three doshas.

00:45:45.490 --> 00:45:47.640 align:middle line:84%
Even if you're
overheated and pitta,

00:45:47.640 --> 00:45:49.920 align:middle line:84%
we wouldn't put
you on iced drinks.

00:45:49.920 --> 00:45:50.681 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:45:50.681 --> 00:45:51.180 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:45:51.180 --> 00:45:53.263 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: We use a lot of
spices that are cooling.

00:45:53.263 --> 00:45:55.070 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Yogurt
is another good one.

00:45:55.070 --> 00:45:57.010 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: Yogurt, if it's very
fresh can be very cooling.

00:45:57.010 --> 00:45:57.635 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:45:57.635 --> 00:45:59.230 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: We make
yogurt drinks--

00:45:59.230 --> 00:45:59.870 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Oh, I love them.

00:45:59.870 --> 00:46:02.203 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: --that are called
lassis that can be very good

00:46:02.203 --> 00:46:05.010 align:middle line:84%
for pitta, if they have the
right spices in them that would

00:46:05.010 --> 00:46:06.650 align:middle line:90%
be cooling spices.

00:46:06.650 --> 00:46:08.140 align:middle line:90%
So we use a lot of dill.

00:46:08.140 --> 00:46:10.360 align:middle line:90%
That's a cooling spice.

00:46:10.360 --> 00:46:11.730 align:middle line:90%
Cumin is very cooling.

00:46:11.730 --> 00:46:15.070 align:middle line:84%
Fennel is very cooling,
coriander or cilantro.

00:46:15.070 --> 00:46:17.790 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Which really,
outside of the dill,

00:46:17.790 --> 00:46:22.020 align:middle line:84%
a lot of those are in
certain chai recipes.

00:46:22.020 --> 00:46:23.570 align:middle line:90%
Some seem to be very hot.

00:46:23.570 --> 00:46:25.500 align:middle line:84%
Others seem to be
much more cooling.

00:46:25.500 --> 00:46:28.230 align:middle line:84%
I make a cooling--
everything you just said.

00:46:28.230 --> 00:46:31.770 align:middle line:10%
>> DESAI: And chai is basically
just a mix of spices that you

00:46:31.770 --> 00:46:32.970 align:middle line:10%
put into your tea.

00:46:32.970 --> 00:46:35.500 align:middle line:10%
So you can definitely
make your own chai

00:46:35.500 --> 00:46:37.370 align:middle line:10%
and just pick your
spices according

00:46:37.370 --> 00:46:40.090 align:middle line:10%
to what you need for
your constitution.

00:46:40.090 --> 00:46:42.010 align:middle line:10%
So if you wanted a
more cooling chai,

00:46:42.010 --> 00:46:43.700 align:middle line:10%
you could put more
cardamom in there.

00:46:43.700 --> 00:46:44.750 align:middle line:10%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:46:44.750 --> 00:46:48.280 align:middle line:10%
>> DESAI: And if you wanted
a more fiery hot chai,

00:46:48.280 --> 00:46:50.750 align:middle line:10%
you could put more black pepper
in there and get it really

00:46:50.750 --> 00:46:51.490 align:middle line:10%
spicy.

00:46:51.490 --> 00:46:55.970 align:middle line:10%
>> REGINA: So might chai
actually be a good morning

00:46:55.970 --> 00:47:01.390 align:middle line:10%
drink or approach to diet for
all of the doshas, really,

00:47:01.390 --> 00:47:04.830 align:middle line:10%
because you can temper
those spice combinations?

00:47:04.830 --> 00:47:06.630 align:middle line:10%
>> DESAI: I think chai
is a good approach.

00:47:06.630 --> 00:47:09.280 align:middle line:10%
It doesn't necessarily
have to have the black tea,

00:47:09.280 --> 00:47:12.620 align:middle line:10%
because the caffeine might not
be appropriate for everybody.

00:47:12.620 --> 00:47:15.690 align:middle line:10%
But the idea of a
warm drink with spices

00:47:15.690 --> 00:47:18.460 align:middle line:10%
appropriate for
your constitution

00:47:18.460 --> 00:47:20.140 align:middle line:10%
would be a great
idea for anybody

00:47:20.140 --> 00:47:22.980 align:middle line:10%
to kind of get themselves
going in the morning,

00:47:22.980 --> 00:47:25.250 align:middle line:10%
wake up the digestive system.

00:47:25.250 --> 00:47:28.060 align:middle line:10%
Instead of throwing something
really heavy down there

00:47:28.060 --> 00:47:30.280 align:middle line:10%
as the first thing you do,
putting some of those nice

00:47:30.280 --> 00:47:35.696 align:middle line:10%
spice-- a tea that has
just some spices in it--

00:47:35.696 --> 00:47:37.070 align:middle line:10%
>> REGINA: Without
the black tea.

00:47:37.070 --> 00:47:37.735 align:middle line:10%
>> DESAI: Not necessarily.

00:47:37.735 --> 00:47:38.500 align:middle line:10%
>> REGINA: Not necessarily.

00:47:38.500 --> 00:47:39.583 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: Not necessarily.

00:47:39.583 --> 00:47:41.385 align:middle line:84%
Some people could
do the black tea.

00:47:41.385 --> 00:47:43.970 align:middle line:84%
It would be a good way to get
your day going, because it kind

00:47:43.970 --> 00:47:46.860 align:middle line:84%
of gets your digestion
to wake up a little.

00:47:46.860 --> 00:47:49.755 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And we'll get to how
people can find out about which

00:47:49.755 --> 00:47:52.255 align:middle line:84%
are appropriate for them toward
the end of our conversation.

00:47:52.255 --> 00:47:53.921 align:middle line:84%
I just wanted to bring
that up because I

00:47:53.921 --> 00:47:55.800 align:middle line:84%
think it's a lovely
way to begin the day.

00:47:55.800 --> 00:47:57.800 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: It is a great
way to begin the day.

00:47:57.800 --> 00:47:59.870 align:middle line:84%
And so should we get back
to the pittas a little bit?

00:47:59.870 --> 00:48:00.620 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Please.

00:48:00.620 --> 00:48:02.720 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: OK.

00:48:02.720 --> 00:48:06.410 align:middle line:84%
The pitta dosha, but mostly
it's just a very energetically

00:48:06.410 --> 00:48:08.780 align:middle line:84%
cooling diet that
we give pittas.

00:48:08.780 --> 00:48:10.340 align:middle line:84%
And then the most
important thing

00:48:10.340 --> 00:48:13.810 align:middle line:84%
for pittas really
lifestyle-wise is

00:48:13.810 --> 00:48:16.690 align:middle line:84%
to not be Type A, to
not be so goal-oriented,

00:48:16.690 --> 00:48:18.680 align:middle line:90%
to have some fun in their life.

00:48:18.680 --> 00:48:20.250 align:middle line:10%
So really when I
work with pittas,

00:48:20.250 --> 00:48:22.270 align:middle line:10%
it's about finding
something that they

00:48:22.270 --> 00:48:24.910 align:middle line:10%
find joyful that they
can be playful about.

00:48:24.910 --> 00:48:28.312 align:middle line:10%
So a lot of times they're
CEOs, and they're working hard,

00:48:28.312 --> 00:48:29.770 align:middle line:10%
and everything is
so goal-oriented.

00:48:29.770 --> 00:48:32.110 align:middle line:10%
And then for their
recreation they're

00:48:32.110 --> 00:48:33.520 align:middle line:10%
playing tennis or something.

00:48:33.520 --> 00:48:33.880 align:middle line:10%
>> REGINA: Something aggressive.

00:48:33.880 --> 00:48:35.410 align:middle line:10%
>> DESAI: Really aggressive.

00:48:35.410 --> 00:48:35.780 align:middle line:10%
>> REGINA: Competitive.

00:48:35.780 --> 00:48:37.830 align:middle line:10%
>> DESAI: They're Type
A. They're on a team.

00:48:37.830 --> 00:48:40.070 align:middle line:10%
And I might steer them into
something a little more

00:48:40.070 --> 00:48:42.364 align:middle line:10%
fun, a little more
playful, and maybe go--

00:48:42.364 --> 00:48:43.155 align:middle line:10%
>> REGINA: Dancing?

00:48:43.155 --> 00:48:44.200 align:middle line:10%
>> DESAI: --dance, yeah.

00:48:44.200 --> 00:48:47.110 align:middle line:10%
Do something fun and more
playful for exercise,

00:48:47.110 --> 00:48:49.440 align:middle line:10%
just because they do need
a little of that balance

00:48:49.440 --> 00:48:51.679 align:middle line:10%
in their life where they're
not so goal-oriented.

00:48:51.679 --> 00:48:54.220 align:middle line:10%
>> REGINA: So what might be the
drug of choice for a very out

00:48:54.220 --> 00:48:58.120 align:middle line:10%
of balance pitta that's
trying to perpetuate itself?

00:48:58.120 --> 00:49:01.360 align:middle line:10%
>> DESAI: Again, I think in
our society we do use a lot

00:49:01.360 --> 00:49:03.330 align:middle line:10%
of caffeine.

00:49:03.330 --> 00:49:04.945 align:middle line:10%
Anything that kind
of keeps you going

00:49:04.945 --> 00:49:06.070 align:middle line:10%
gives you high performance.

00:49:06.070 --> 00:49:07.150 align:middle line:10%
>> REGINA: Yeah.

00:49:07.150 --> 00:49:10.150 align:middle line:10%
>> DESAI: Because they just want
to keep going 20 hours a day.

00:49:10.150 --> 00:49:11.150 align:middle line:90%
They don't want to stop.

00:49:11.150 --> 00:49:14.400 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So really the kind
of '80s, '90s cocaine thing was

00:49:14.400 --> 00:49:16.460 align:middle line:84%
very pitta-oriented
in our society.

00:49:16.460 --> 00:49:18.750 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: Very pitta-oriented.

00:49:18.750 --> 00:49:22.640 align:middle line:84%
Both vata and pitta tend
to be in our society a lot.

00:49:22.640 --> 00:49:23.350 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:49:23.350 --> 00:49:24.970 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: One thing
I tell people,

00:49:24.970 --> 00:49:27.525 align:middle line:84%
because I see this a lot, is
they'll get themselves going

00:49:27.525 --> 00:49:28.900 align:middle line:84%
in the morning
with the caffeine,

00:49:28.900 --> 00:49:31.770 align:middle line:84%
they'll keep themselves going
all day with several cups

00:49:31.770 --> 00:49:34.470 align:middle line:84%
of coffee, and then
because they're so wired,

00:49:34.470 --> 00:49:37.250 align:middle line:84%
they've thrown themselves so
heavily into their sympathetic

00:49:37.250 --> 00:49:40.852 align:middle line:84%
nervous system, when they get
home they can't turn it off.

00:49:40.852 --> 00:49:41.560 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:49:41.560 --> 00:49:44.640 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: And so then they
have to drink alcohol to kind

00:49:44.640 --> 00:49:46.915 align:middle line:84%
of depress their system
to bring them down.

00:49:46.915 --> 00:49:47.540 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:49:47.540 --> 00:49:50.280 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: So they're in
this awful catch-22 where

00:49:50.280 --> 00:49:52.530 align:middle line:84%
they're stimulating themselves
to get themselves going

00:49:52.530 --> 00:49:54.870 align:middle line:84%
in the morning, and then
they're depressing themselves

00:49:54.870 --> 00:49:57.030 align:middle line:84%
at the end of the day to bring
themselves down so they can

00:49:57.030 --> 00:49:57.570 align:middle line:90%
sleep.

00:49:57.570 --> 00:49:58.195 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:49:58.195 --> 00:50:01.120 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: And it's part of
our society, unfortunately.

00:50:01.120 --> 00:50:03.270 align:middle line:84%
We end up in this
cycle, and it's

00:50:03.270 --> 00:50:04.665 align:middle line:90%
very hard on the nervous system.

00:50:04.665 --> 00:50:05.540 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Very hard.

00:50:05.540 --> 00:50:07.020 align:middle line:90%
And it's hard on the adrenals.

00:50:07.020 --> 00:50:08.870 align:middle line:90%
So now let's talk about kapha.

00:50:08.870 --> 00:50:09.610 align:middle line:90%
>> DESAI: OK.

00:50:09.610 --> 00:50:12.410 align:middle line:84%
So kaphas actually have a
lot of that Earth energy,

00:50:12.410 --> 00:50:14.110 align:middle line:90%
a lot of that grounded energy.

00:50:14.110 --> 00:50:17.010 align:middle line:84%
They tend to get all those
mucousy kinds of problems

00:50:17.010 --> 00:50:19.180 align:middle line:84%
and overweight and
high cholesterol

00:50:19.180 --> 00:50:20.510 align:middle line:90%
and all that kind of stuff.

00:50:20.510 --> 00:50:22.410 align:middle line:84%
So they do better
with a lighter diet.

00:50:22.410 --> 00:50:25.620 align:middle line:84%
So kaphas actually can eat
raw food, if they want to.

00:50:25.620 --> 00:50:28.830 align:middle line:84%
Not all kaphas, but if they have
a very good digestive system

00:50:28.830 --> 00:50:32.690 align:middle line:84%
they do well with more
of a salad-y diet.

00:50:32.690 --> 00:50:34.975 align:middle line:84%
They could do a little more
raw foods, a lighter diet.

00:50:34.975 --> 00:50:36.266 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: A lot of vegetables?

00:50:36.266 --> 00:50:39.160 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: Lots of
vegetables, lots of fruits,

00:50:39.160 --> 00:50:41.370 align:middle line:90%
lighter on the carbohydrates.

00:50:41.370 --> 00:50:43.770 align:middle line:84%
They don't do well with a
lot of cards, especially

00:50:43.770 --> 00:50:45.430 align:middle line:90%
heavy things like wheat.

00:50:45.430 --> 00:50:47.680 align:middle line:10%
Wheat would be very
heavy for kapha.

00:50:47.680 --> 00:50:50.830 align:middle line:10%
A hot bowl of oatmeal would be
a little too heavy for kapha.

00:50:50.830 --> 00:50:53.910 align:middle line:10%
They might start their day out
with a little something lighter

00:50:53.910 --> 00:50:54.430 align:middle line:10%
than that.

00:50:54.430 --> 00:50:56.650 align:middle line:84%
They might start out with
some just fruit salad

00:50:56.650 --> 00:50:58.460 align:middle line:84%
in the morning or
something lighter.

00:50:58.460 --> 00:51:01.050 align:middle line:84%
They do well with
protein, though.

00:51:01.050 --> 00:51:05.820 align:middle line:84%
I think all three doshas to
some degree need some protein.

00:51:05.820 --> 00:51:07.280 align:middle line:90%
Kaphas can do protein.

00:51:07.280 --> 00:51:09.520 align:middle line:84%
But then if they do
too much protein--

00:51:09.520 --> 00:51:12.720 align:middle line:84%
so if they're living in Texas
and having their 16-ounce

00:51:12.720 --> 00:51:13.670 align:middle line:90%
steak--

00:51:13.670 --> 00:51:15.330 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Or their
52-ounce steak.

00:51:15.330 --> 00:51:16.430 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: --or their
52-ounce steak--

00:51:16.430 --> 00:51:18.096 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: It's free,
if you can eat it.

00:51:18.096 --> 00:51:21.250 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: --with the extra
large Idaho potato and a lot

00:51:21.250 --> 00:51:23.169 align:middle line:84%
of butter, that would
not be a kapha diet.

00:51:23.169 --> 00:51:24.960 align:middle line:84%
That's where you're
getting your high blood

00:51:24.960 --> 00:51:27.300 align:middle line:84%
pressure and your high
cholesterol, too heavy

00:51:27.300 --> 00:51:28.802 align:middle line:90%
for kaphas.

00:51:28.802 --> 00:51:30.260 align:middle line:84%
They're the ones
who really do need

00:51:30.260 --> 00:51:32.514 align:middle line:84%
to eat more of a
salad-y type of diet.

00:51:32.514 --> 00:51:33.930 align:middle line:84%
Or if they don't
want to do salad,

00:51:33.930 --> 00:51:37.010 align:middle line:84%
they can do more cooked
vegetables, a lighter diet,

00:51:37.010 --> 00:51:40.807 align:middle line:84%
maybe some carbohydrate
content, but not too much.

00:51:40.807 --> 00:51:41.390 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: OK.

00:51:41.390 --> 00:51:45.770 align:middle line:84%
And when they go out of balance
into the depressive state,

00:51:45.770 --> 00:51:47.490 align:middle line:84%
for example, which
you earlier said

00:51:47.490 --> 00:51:52.410 align:middle line:84%
they might be prone to, how
do they tend to self-medicate?

00:51:52.410 --> 00:51:56.800 align:middle line:84%
>> DESAI: Well, I think a lot
of people medicate by initially

00:51:56.800 --> 00:52:01.260 align:middle line:84%
thinking that alcohol will help,
because alcohol initially gives

